title: salmon balls in mushroom sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients except the soup.
Shape salmon into balls.
Put in baking dish or casserole; cover with soup/milk mixture.
Makes 15 balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot pepper mustard
directions: Cut tops off of peppers.
Grind (or process in food processor) peppers, seeds and all.
Place onions in grinder (or food processor), enough for them to be chopped.

title: broccoli oven omelet
directions: Beat eggs with wire whisk in 2 1/2-quart bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in broccoli, onion, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, the milk, salt, basil and garlic powder.
Pour into ungreased rectangular 11 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cook, uncovered, in 325° oven until set, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamsickle cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs; beat well. Add the sour cream and vanilla; mix well. Place 1 cup of mixture in a small bowl and stir in the orange extract and yellow and red food coloring. Pour the remaining cream cheese mixture into pie crust. Drop the orange cream cheese mixture into it by spoonfuls and swirl with a knife to create a marble effect.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm around the edge. (The center will be slightly loose.) Allow to cool for 1 hour. Cover and chill for at least 8 hours before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put ingredients, except vanilla, in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over approximately 10 to 12 cups popped popcorn. Mix until well coated.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Arrange peach halves, round side up, in uncooked pie crust. Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon and cream.
Pour over peaches and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: uncle danny's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, mix together first 4 ingredients, and bring to a boil.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: harvard beets
directions: Wash beets; cook in boiling water until soft.
Remove skins and cut beets in thin slices, small cubes or fancy shapes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup vinegar and 2 tablespoons cornstarch together and let boil five minutes.
Pour over beets and let stand on back of range 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: stuffed pork chops(costolette di maiale ripieni)
directions: Have butcher cut a
pocket in each chop.
Place 1 slice Mozzarella cheese, Prosciutto, salt and pepper in each pocket; close.
Secure with
string
or
toothpicks.
Roll
chops into bread crumbs and dip
into
egg.
Fry
in
oil
on medium heat until golden on each
side.
Place in baking dish and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Combine sugar, soy sauce, wine, vinegar and catsup in saucepan; bring to a boil (stir constantly).

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Shake in large plastic bag.
Dip legs and thigh pieces into 1/3 cup oil and 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Allow to stand 1 hour on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, turn over for additional 15 minutes.
May be baked with or without skin, but with skin is tastier.

title: my pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in bowl.
Stir in pumpkin, milk and egg.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until firm.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: delicious raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins with water to cover plus a small amount.
Cook until fluffy, about 1/2 hour.
Do not drain.
Combine sugar and flour and add enough water to make a thin paste.
Add to the raisins, bring to a boil and stir well.
Pour in a pastry shell, add a top crust and slit.
Bake in a moderate oven until brown.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add alternately with buttermilk, beating until smooth. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans. Pour batter into pans; bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: swiss onion dip
directions: Mix together.
Pour in baking dish.
On top, sprinkle chopped pecans.
On top, dot with butter, optional.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar and garlic powder.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
To the hot noodles, add sour cream, cream cheese and green onions.
Arrange meat mixture and noodles in alternate layers, using large, round casserole.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice and 1/2 onion soup.
Put in 7 x 10-inch baking dish. Mix water and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over rice mixture. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 of onion soup mix on top of cream of chicken soup.
Arrange chicken on top.
Sprinkle small amount of salt over chicken (you may use paprika).
Cover and cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil last 15 minutes to brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Thoroughly mix pie filling and eggs.
"Dump" in rest of ingredients and stir well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for one hour.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugars, dressing and vanilla at medium speed.
Add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of the batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Stir oleo and egg into macaroni.
Mix mustard and salt with 1 tablespoon hot water and add to milk.
Add 2 1/2 cups cheese into macaroni and pour into buttered casserole.
Add milk mixture, sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 350° 45 minutes or until crusty.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Rub in butter until blended.
Add raisins.
Add eggs and enough milk to make a dough. Chill 1 hour.
Roll out on floured board to thickness of 1/4 inch. Cut into 2 1/2 inch rounds (with a glass).
Bake on greased griddle or in frying pan (use butter) on low heat.
Turn to lightly brown on each side.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put butter and sugar in top of double boiler.
Add 1 cup milk. Heat over boiling water until milk is scalded.
Mix flour and salt.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk, then stir this mixture into contents of double boiler.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes.
Beat egg yolks; add to double boiler.
Cook for 1 minute.
Cool slightly; pour into baked pie shell.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix the melted margarine and crushed Oreos.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together both cream cheeses, the powdered sugar and half the Cool Whip.
Put this over cookie base.
Mix together both puddings and milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Put the other half of the Cool Whip over the top.
Then sprinkle a few crushed Oreos on top of the Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and vanilla until light.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat milk and butter just to boiling point.
Gradually add to egg mixture. Pour into 2 layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: mixed nut brittle
directions: Butter 2 large baking sheets.
Butter the sides of a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and 1/2 cup margarine or butter.
Cook over medium heat to boiling, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
This should take 5 minutes, then cook 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Stir frequently 15 to 20 minutes; remove from heat.
Quickly sprinkle sifted baking soda over mixture, stirring constantly.
Immediately pour into baking sheets; let cool.
Pull apart with forks.
Store tightly covered.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing and milk with mixer until well blended. Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate several hours.

title: sylvia's lasagne
directions: Sauce:
Brown all meat; crumble and drain fat.
Add garlic, French soup and bell pepper.
Mix well.
Cook for a few minutes. Add tomatoes and sauce, Italian seasoning and wine vinegar. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and flour until stiff.
Add sugar.
Put on pie and bake until golden.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornmeal dumplings
directions: Mix cornmeal and flour well and mix with enough water to make it stick together.
It should be very stiff.
Roll into balls about the size of an egg and cook on top of greens, collards, turnips or cabbage.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes on boiling greens.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion, celery, parsley and mushrooms (if fresh) and chopped pepper.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: glazed strawberry yogurt squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine with a fork until crumbly; reserve 1/4 cup.
Press remaining mixture firmly in bottom of ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients except fruit rolls; pour over baked layer. Cover top completely with unrolled fruit rolls, cutting to fit, if necessary.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake until pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 20 minutes longer. Cool 15 minutes.

title: kiplings
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Pinch off small amounts and roll into crescent shapes. Bake at 250° until brown. Cool slightly. Put each cookie in a small brown paper bag with confectioners sugar and gently shake to coat them. Cool on wax paper.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine cocoa, flour and water.
Cook until thickens, then add sugar.
Best when served on hot buttered biscuits.

title: peanut butter pieces
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the ingredients, except for the chocolate chips and 1/4 cup of peanut butter.
Mix well with spoon.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/4 cup of peanut butter in saucepan.
Mix and pour over mixture in pan. Refrigerate until hardened.
Cut into pieces at room temperature.

title: charlotte's tortellini salad
directions: In pot of boiling water, blanch broccoli, cauliflower and tomato.
Peel tomato and cut into medium chunks.
Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Rinse and let cool.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Add dressing and mix well. Refrigerate 1/2 hour and serve.

title: brown rice pilaf
directions: Bring broth to a boil in a heavy saucepan; stir in rice and remaining ingredients except almonds.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in almonds.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes thoroughly. Bake and let cool.

Chop into small pieces. Heat soup, milk and spices. Add potatoes. Use low heat because this will burn easily. Add cheese just before serving. Can serve with bacon bits, crackers, green onions, sour cream, etc. Makes about 6 servings.

title: country meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef in a large cooking bowl; add egg and ketchup. Add chopped onion and grated cheese.
Crumble saltine crackers into meat loaf mixture.
Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Cook for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: no fail custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 425° for 10 minutes then 400° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cereal glop plop
directions: Boil Karo syrup, sugar and peanut butter 3 minutes, then add cereal.
Mix over heat, then plop on wax paper.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Add 1 teaspoon oil to a large nonstick skillet; place skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add chicken and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove chicken from skillet; set aside and keep warm. Wipe drippings from skillet with a paper towel.

title: nonna rosetta's bucatini all'amatriciana
directions: Begin cooking pasta in boiling water.
Heat half the oil in frying pan and saute onion and chili until soft.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 7 minutes.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: *Or you may use 2 (8 ounce) guacamole dip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash 1/4-inch thick. Mix soup, cheese, onion, garlic and mayonnaise together and stir squash into it.
Put in a long, flat Pyrex dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and pour the stick of melted oleo over the crackers.
Mix well and cover the squash with it. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Beat the next 4 ingredients together and pour over unbaked cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sherried beef
directions: Cut steak in bite size pieces and remove fat.
Mix all ingredients together and cook, covered, 3 hours at 325°.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt caramels with water in top of double boiler.
Add pecans and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Place in freezer until firm and candy will peel off paper.

title: low-fat baked manicotti
directions: Cook onion, zucchini and celery in skillet sprayed with Pam. Add soup, chicken, spinach and cottage cheese.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Blend well butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Blend well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda together. (Note:
Add buttermilk and sifted flour mixture alternately until consumed.)
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done, in three cake tins.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add peanut butter and eggs and mix well.
Sift soda and flour.
Combine with creamed mixture. Shape into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Wrap and chill.
Slice in 1/8-inch thickness.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Crush approximately 1 1/2 packages graham crackers.
Melt butter and add to crumbs.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and spread out evenly and pack tightly.
Beat together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread this over crust.
Add sliced bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle with pecans and cherries and pour chocolate syrup on top. Refrigerate before serving.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook and dice
meat.
Cook
raisins
in a little bit of water until tender.
Mix	all
ingredients
in tub and stir it all together.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: mud hens
directions: Mix together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 1 egg white; add 1
cup	of
light
brown sugar and 1 cup of chopped nuts. Spread
on top of first mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade winter stew
directions: Combine meat and vegetables in an electric slow cooker.
Add bay leaves, tomato sauce, broth, wine and water.
Cook 6 hours on high; 7 hours or longer on low.

title: seasonal greens salad
directions: Refrigerate 4 salad plates so that they are nice and cold. Spread butter lightly on bread.
Next, spread Blue cheese on bread.
Broil until cheese melts and bread is slightly toasted.

title: chicken-potato soup
directions: *The frozen, boneless chicken pieces that you can buy in bulk work very well. Cook them in the microwave as you chop the vegetable.
Don't forget to add the cooking juices to the soup.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to package.
Add all other ingredients to macaroni and combine with hamburger.
Place in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: no-roll pie crust
directions: Combine milk and oil in measuring cup.
Whip with a fork and pour at once over flour.
Mix with fork until flour is completely dampened.
Press with fingers into 9-inch pie plate.

title: summer fondue
directions: Put all ingredients in fondue pot about 10 minutes before time to serve.
Heat, stirring often, until very hot and bubbly. Toasted bread, grapes, Spam or any other food you like may be dipped in the hot fondue and eaten.

title: meat ball dinner
directions: Mix together egg, 1/2 cup milk and bread crumbs.
Add, and mix thoroughly, salt, pepper, dry mustard, celery salt, nutmeg, onion and ground beef.
Shape into 20 meat balls.
Brown in small amount of fat.
Cook slowly, turning often.
Remove from skillet.

title: super-easy pate
directions: Combine. Pack into crock or small dish and serve with crackers.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and 1/2 of tomato sauce. Form into loaf and bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed on box.
Crumble.
Layer in punch bowl, starting with cake crumble, vanilla pudding, strawberries, blueberries, pineapple, mandarin oranges, walnuts and Cool Whip.
Top cake with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: prune bread
directions: Combine raisins, prunes and boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Add soda to raisin mixture and dump into cake batter.
Stir until mixed.
Grease and flour loaf pans or cans.
Soup cans make nice little round loaves.
If you use cans, place them on a cookie sheet.
Fill about 1/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix water and yeast in a large bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour and 1 tablespoon sugar to yeast mixture.
Knead flour mixture by working in 1/2 cup flour.
Divide dough and shape pretzels.
Brush egg on top of pretzels.
Sprinkle coarse salt on pretzels.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef and olive spread
directions: In a small bowl, soften onion in milk.
Stir in cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add beef and olives; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on crackers.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer for 3/4 hour.

title: pinto beans and rice
directions: Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, 2 hours; add more water if necessary.
After 2 hours, add 1/2 stick margarine and pepper to taste.
Cover; cook another hour on low heat.
Serve over white rice.

title: cheese and rice casserole
directions: Combine soups, pimentos, onion and 1/4 cup parsley.
Heat. Pour over rice and mix well.
Turn into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese and remaining parsley.
Bake 20 minutes at 450° or until hot and bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water and 7-Up and add marshmallows, bananas, pineapple and pecans.
Put in dish and let set up.
Combine juice, egg, sugar, flour and butter and cook until thick.
Allow to cool, then layer on top of jello mixture.
Whip Dream Whip and spread over top.

title: katie's nut rolls
directions: If too stiff, add a little hot milk.

title: heavenly mock lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Saute beef in butter.
Stir in tomato sauce.
In another bowl combine the next four items.
In 2 quart casserole layer as follows:
1/2 of noodles, then cover with cheese mixture, remaining noodles, pour the melted butter over then pour on meat sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8-10.
Can be made ahead and frozen before serving.

title: granola crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Lightly grease 15 x 10 x 1 jellyroll pan. Combine oats, coconut, pecans, sunflower seeds, wheat germ, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl. Stir together oil, water, honey and vanilla in small bowl. Pour over oat mixture and mix well. Spread mixture evenly in prepared pan. Bake in oven for 1 hour at 300°, stirring every 15 minutes, until mixture is golden brown and slightly crunchy. Stir in raisins and dates.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine corn syrup and pudding in a bowl, blending well. Stir in evaporated milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Chill about 10 minutes.
Spread on German Chocolate Cake.

title: pasta alla puttanesca
directions: In a medium saucepan, put enough oil to coat bottom of pot. Add crushed garlic and brown until golden.
Add chopped olives (drained), rinsed capers, basil, parsley and pepper.
Saute a few seconds, then add tomatoes and salt to taste; stir.
Cover and turn heat on low.
Cook for about 40 minutes, stirring often.

title: quick fruit topping
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juice.
Mix pudding into juice, stirring until well blended and thick; stir in fruit.
Serve as topping for cheese cake or angel food cake.

title: mmm good chili
directions: In large Dutch oven, crumble and brown meat.
Add vegetables and chili powder.
Cook until onions are slightly tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add beans.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients with electric mixer.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into a bowl of powdered sugar.
Roll dough around until coated with sugar.
Pat into a thin cookie and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
They will not be dark brown.

title: breakfast bunkil cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in pan then mix the following ingredients through the batter - 1/2 c. nuts, 1/4 c. sugar and 2 tsp. cinnamon.
Bake in bundt cake pan at 350° for 35 - 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a mixer bowl, beat together eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Spread in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan; bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: In a bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted flour and salt alternately with combined buttermilk and soda.
Blend in orange rind, raisins, walnuts and coconut.
Turn into a well-greased and floured tube pan (10-inch).
Bake in slow oven (300°) until a cake tester comes away dry (about 1 1/2 hours). Remove from oven, leave cake in pan.

title: lemon daffodil torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, rind and food coloring (if desired). Chill.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together shortening and the sugar.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well and cover and chill.
Form dough into 1-inch balls; roll each in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until dark golden brown. Remove cookies to wire rack and cool.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: artichoke (or zucchini) nibbler
directions: Drain 1 jar artichokes into frypan. Add onion and garlic. Saute lightly. Chop artichokes (or grate zucchini).
Set aside.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
To prepare spiced tea, use 2 teaspoons mix to each cup of boiling water.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all ingredients to beaten eggs and mix together.
Pour mixture into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake for 25 minutes at 350 or 375°.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Simmer 15 minutes in skillet.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin and pound thin the chicken breast. In small skillet, combine spinach, onions, mushrooms and 1 teaspoon water.
Cook, covered, over medium heat, until onions are tender (about 2 minutes).
Sprinkle chicken breast with garlic, paprika, salt and pepper.
Spread cooked vegetables over chicken.
Roll up tightly to enclose filling.
Sprinkle milk over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and pat with fingers to cover.
Place chicken in a small baking pan.
Bake until chicken is golden brown and cooked through (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Arrange batter (blend other ingredients) and apple mixture in layers in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan, beginning with batter mixture and ending with apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
(You can add 1 tablespoon flour to last apples that you put on top of cake so they do not sink!)

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread on dish:
cottage cheese, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Add in order:
salsa, Cheddar cheese, tomato, black olives and green onion.
Chill and serve with taco chips.

title: sour cream dinner rolls
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until butter melts. Cool to 105° to 115°. Combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm water in a glass liquid measuring cup. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir together yeast mixture, sour cream mixture, eggs and flour in a large bowl until well blended. Chill, covered, for 8 hours. Divide dough into fourths and shape each portion into a ball. Roll each into 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface. Cut dough with a 2 1/2 to 3-inch round cutter. Brush rounds evenly with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Make a crease across each round with a knife and fold in half. Gently press edges to seal. Place rolls in a 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan with sides touching. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, for 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in top of double boiler over hot water.
Gradually add sugar.
Add slowly, stirring constantly, the evaporated milk.
Add salt and vanilla.

title: stollen(german yeast dough cake)
directions: Mix flour, yeast and milk; knead and then let rise.
Using large mixing bowl, soften yeast in milk.
Mix flour, yeast and milk.
Mix in butter.
Mix in raisins and mix in korinten (very small raisins).
Mix in sugar.
Mix in almonds, lemon peel, citron, salt and 2 eggs.
Knead flour, yeast and milk dough. First let rise, the mix in other ingredients.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a 7 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix the chicken, celery, scallions, green peppers and avocado. Combine the mayonnaise, cayenne, salt, pepper, lemon juice and sour cream.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Pour the dressing over the chicken mixture and toss lightly so that all is well-coated with dressing.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook to soft ball stage (235°) without stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans. Stir gently until pecans are well coated and mixture becomes creamy.
Turn out on wax paper and separate as they cool.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Beat sugar and Wesson oil; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Then add sour cream.
Blend well.
Add yellow cake mix.
Into greased tube pan, pour half the batter.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts; sprinkle over top of batter in pan. Then add remaining batter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Glaze with powdered sugar glaze.

title: seven layers of heaven
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Pour the melted butter evenly over the bottom of a 9-inch square baking pan.
Spread the graham cracker crumbs evenly over the butter, then layer with the coconut, chocolate chips, then the peanut butter chips, one on top of the other, in the order listed.
Drizzle the sweetened condensed milk over the top layer and sprinkle with the walnuts. Bake for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: creamed chicken over biscuits
directions: Place potatoes and carrots in a small saucepan. Cover with water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 8-10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Drain and set aside. In a large skillet, melt butter. Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually whisk in milk. Add the bouillon and pepper. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in the chicken, peas and potato mixture; heat through. Serve over biscuits. Yield: 2 servings.

title: play dough you can eat(for kids to make)
directions: Wash your hands! Mix the pudding and milk. Add the peanut butter. Mix in powdered milk until the texture is like play dough. Break off a portion about the size of a golf ball.
Mold it like play dough. After playing with the play dough, enjoy eating it.

title: onion soup(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Put butter in large skillet, saute onion until golden, not browned, about 8 minutes.
In medium saucepan, combine the bouillon and sauteed onion.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: rush hour rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown rice and seasonings in oil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add chicken broth and water. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice is cooked and water is absorbed.
Add chicken, vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ethereal mushrooms
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Put in mushrooms; cover.
Simmer 5 hours.
Take cover off.
Simmer 4 more hours.
These cook up to a very dark color but are wonderful.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Add mustard, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce to soup. In another bowl, mix meat, egg, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and 1/4 cup soup mix.
Make patties and brown.
Add 1/2 cup water to soup mix.
Pour over patties and simmer 20 minutes.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix beef and onion mixture with pork and beans, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Place in casserole dish and top with Hungry Jack biscuits.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into rectangle baking dish.
Bake at 325° for glass dish for 1 hour and at 350° for metal cake pan.

title: settler's baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion; drain well.
Mix all remaining ingredients and add to beef, bacon and onion.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or cook several hours in a crock-pot.

title: hamburger chop suey or chow mein
directions: Add to meat mixture.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve hot over cooked rice for chop suey or fried noodles for chow mein.

title: egg nog
directions: Blend all ingredients together and serve chilled.

title: beef steak(philippine style)
directions: Combine soy sauce, lemon juice and pepper and pour over beef slices; mix well.
Marinate several hours.
Saut onion in hot oil until transparent.
Transfer to platter.
Pan-fry beef slices a few at a time until brown on both sides.
Serve hot with sauted onion.

title: chicken and shrimp over wild rice
directions: In a large saute pan, add oil; heat it.
Dice (strip into quarters) chicken, and flour pieces.
Add to oil and brown.
Remove chicken and place aside.
Flour shrimp; add to hot oil.
Brown both sides.
Remove shrimp and put aside with chicken.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Check with toothpick.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: pickled okra
directions: Scrub okra and pack in pint jars.
Place one clove garlic and one head of dill in each jar.
Make brine of water, vinegar and salt; heat to boil.
Pour brine over okra.
Seal jars and let stand 3 to 4 weeks.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and add to melted margarine.
Add peaches, but do not stir.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes until it begins to brown.
Serves 8 people.

title: long john silver's fish batter
directions: Mix well.
Flour fish before dipping. Deep-fry.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: First you pick the berries.
Then you wash and slice them. Sprinkle a little sugar on them.

title: hobo cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, add dry ingredients and mix together.
Add vinegar, vanilla, oil and water to dry ingredients. Mix well with fork, making sure you get all the corners.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hungarian paprika chicken
directions: Brown onion in cooking oil.
Remove from pan and let drain. Brown chicken in essence remaining in pan.
Remove chicken and pour out grease.
Put onion, green pepper, tomatoes and chicken back in pan and cook until tender (approximately 1 hour, depending on size of pieces).
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to sauce and blend for approximately 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: almost impossible peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
I think you will be surprised as I was at the results when the recipe was given to me.

title: okra pickles
directions: Pack okra firmly in jars.
Put garlic clove in each jar. Combine other ingredients and boil.
Pour boiling brine over okra and seal jars.
Process in boiling water bath about 180° to 200° for 10 minutes.
Let ripen several weeks before opening.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: turkey-hummus dip
directions: Peel and chop the garlic.
Squeeze the juice from the lemons. Put everything, except the paprika, into a blender and blend it until smooth.
Add a little water if you need to.
Pour onto a dish and sprinkle with the paprika.
Serve as a dip with pita pockets.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Cover the first 4 ingredients with water and refrigerate overnight.
The next 3 ingredients, heat until dissolved.
Cool. Wash and drain cucumbers.
Place in containers and pour syrup to cover and freeze.

title: biscuits with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in pan or on barbecue.
Mix all other ingredients together in large bowl.
Tear biscuits in pieces and mix with liquid.
Pour over pork chops and cook at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients and make 2 long rolls.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Bake 4 or 5 minutes at 400°.

title: mushroom filled burgers
directions: Heat grill.
Combine hamburger, turkey, onion, catsup and garlic powder; blend well.
Shape into 8 patties.
Place 4 patties on waxed paper.
Top each patty with 1/4 of the mushrooms and 1 of the remaining patties; press edges to seal.
When ready to barbecue, place stuffed patties on grill.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, turning once.
Serve patties on buns with mayonnaise, tomato and lettuce.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Combine and mix well the first 9 ingredients.
Spread in an ungreased square baking pan (glass). Combine last 3 ingredients and stir well.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm or cold with ice cream or topping.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix together and freeze solid.
Let thaw to slush and serve in sherbet glasses.
Can be refrozen and will keep several weeks.

title: buttermilk donuts
directions: Mix and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Roll on thin side (about 1-inch).
Test shortening with small amount of dough.

title: put in bottom of cake pan taco casserole
directions: Add taco seasoning, beans and sauce to browned hamburger.
Put in bottom of cake pan, chop tomatoes and sprinkle on top, sprinkle on shredded cheese.
Crunch doritos and sprinkle on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until mixture bubbles.
Serve with sour cream, lettuce, black olives etc.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Put uncooked macaroni in bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Beat egg in milk.
Pour over macaroni.
Brown hamburg with onion and green pepper.
Spread over the macaroni.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour pizza or spaghetti sauce, adding water, over this. Put Mozzarella cheese over the top; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. You can add mushrooms if you like.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and then add wet ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pan. You may use two 9-inch tins or a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot sweet potatoes
directions: Grease casserole.
Boil sugar, cornstarch, orange peel, apricot nectar, water and spice.
Pour over potatotes.
Add apricots, pecans and one Tbsp. butter.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 25 minutes (or for fresh sweet potatoes, 1 hour).

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1/2 margarine and add crumbs; press in pan.
Beat eggs, sugar, 1/2 margarine and vanilla until creamy.
Spread over crumbs.
Add layer of bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip and top with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese and dressing mix; spread on crust.
Chop any vegetables in small pieces and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: irresistible onion rings
directions: Slice onion into rings (1/2-inch). Heat oil in pan. Beat milk and egg together. Mix all dry ingredients together. Dip onion in egg mixture, then flour mixture.
Deep-fry until golden. Drain on paper towel.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls and press.
Bake at 375° until brown.
(They burn easily.)

title: kindergarten ice cream
directions: You will also need a small coffee can and large coffee can (empty) with lids.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter 12 x 8-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Slice apples into dish. Crumble with pastry blender flour, oleo and sugar.
Pour evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm topped with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda, in a very large punch bowl. Tint to desired color. Slowly add soda. Float ice ring and serve. One recipe serves 35. Requires ice ring made ahead.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix the milk with the lime juice in a large mixing bowl.
In another bowl, whip the egg whites until you can turn the bowl over without them falling out.
Add the egg whites to the bowl with milk and lime juice.
Mix slowly with a whisk so as not to deflate the whites.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Freeze.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Add marshmallows and sour cream, also chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix well and refrigerate for several hours.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle Toll House semi-sweet morsels and nuts.
Spread into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: poulet en cocotte(chicken in a pot)
directions: You need 8-inch frying pan, spatula, wax paper and large freezer bags or container.

title: kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa into bite size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Heat in a 2-quart pan and serve warm.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain the pineapple. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of pineapple juice. If the pineapple juice does not measure a cup, finish with water. Bring the liquid to a boiling point. When dissolved, add 1 cup Coca-Cola, cream cheese, drained pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: hanky-panks
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain and add onion.
Add Velveeta.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Place mixture onto bread.
Bake at 350° until bread is crisp.
Freeze leftovers on bread.
Heat in oven.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add buttermilk.
Stir well.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix until blended.
Knead for 1 minute or until smooth. Roll to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut; place on greased pan.
Let rise for at least 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Will keep in refrigerator in bulk for 4 days.
Makes good cinnamon rolls.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour pan.
Beat margarine and cream cheese well.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Spoon into pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until done.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: virgin strawberry kiwi margarita
directions: Place water, orange juice, lime juice and soft drink mix in a blender.
Cover and blend until drink mix is dissolved.
Add ice cubes.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pudding and pie
directions: Mix together and when it starts to boil, add beaten egg yolk. Boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter. Cool slightly and put in baked
pie shell. Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: tomato dumpling
directions: Smash tomatoes in saucepan and add sugar, then water.
Mix together.
Put on heat.
Bring to boil.
Mix Jiffy mix as box says.
Take mix by spoonful and drop into boiling tomatoes; let cook for 1/2 hour until done.
Let stand in covered pan 15 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple, banana dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press down evenly in bottom.
Arrange banana slices over crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth, gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over bananas.
Spoon pineapple over puddings.
Spread whipped topping over all.
Refrigerate 3 hours or longer.

title: miniature cream cheese
directions: Beat until fluffy cream cheese, eggs, sugar, and vanilla. Place vanilla wafer in cup cake pan in cup cake liner.
Spoon mixture in 1/2 fill.
Bake at 350° for 10-20 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Top with any canned pie filling.
Gingersnaps with apple or peach filling may be used as well. Excellent!!! Refrigerate in tins.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Blend shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar in large bowl. Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 c. M & M's.
Drop from tsp. on ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate tops with remaining candy.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lazy day lasagna(casserole)
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute 1 chopped onion and green pepper, cut in strips, in 2 tablespoons of butter for 3 minutes.
Add lean ground chuck and brown meat, breaking up meat with spoon as it cooks.
Add salt, m.s.g., pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce and water.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar, add eggs and vanilla.
Continue beating.
Add flour mixture.
Fold in dates, nuts and chopped cherries with a wooden spoon.
Make into tablespoon size balls and roll in crushed cornflakes.
Top with 1/4 cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden on greased sheet.

title: pink punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in boiling water.
Add juices (do not dilute juices).
Freeze.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Beat egg and add to dry ingredients.
Add fruit cocktail.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to hour.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown flour in lard to a golden brown, stirring constantly, to prevent burning or lumping.
Add 1/2 chopped seasoning to browned flour; saute for 1 minute.
Add this mixture to the 3 quarts of boiling water; mix.
Add remaining seasoning and bouillon cubes; boil for about 10 minutes.
Put in oysters; simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste, then bring to rapid boil.
Add file; mix well.
Take off heat.
Let set for at least 15 minutes. Serve over boiled rice.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 1 cup additional liquid made up of drained juice from crushed pineapple and water.
Mix well and refrigerate until jelled slightly.
Then add crushed pineapple and carrots.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sigilinda's egg antipasto
directions: Chop the anchovies, capers, garlic and parsley.
Mix with the tuna or salmon.
Add mayonnaise.
If you are making the mayonnaise, use 2 egg yolks.
(For mayonnaise recipe, see our Sauces section.)

title: hot dog stew(ww ii stew)
directions: Cut dogs in pieces.
Chop potatoes, pepper and onion.
Brown all in skillet.
Add a can of tomatoes; fill skillet with water. Sprinkle in some flour; let simmer about 20 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: In a plastic container or ice cube tray, freeze milk until almost solid.
Turn into container of a blender.
Hull strawberries.
Add to blender with sugar and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth and frothy.
Serve immediately or pour into a plastic bowl and freeze until mixture forms a 1 inch thick frozen shell at the edge of bowl.
Stir and serve with spoon as a frosty snack.

title: stupid pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Combine crackers, vanilla, baking powder and pecans. Fold into egg white mixture.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 360° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, pie looks very pale in color and toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
Cool completely.
Prior to serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: cherry salad
directions: Strawberry pie filling can also be used in place of cherry.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 1-inch oil in skillet.
Combine ingredients until moistened.
Fry heaping teaspoonfuls of batter a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: copper carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender-crisp.
Drain and cool. Combine with onion and green pepper. Combine remaining ingredients and mix with vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 2 days. Will keep 8 to 10 days in refrigerator.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine and toss all ingredients.
Just before serving pour on Catalina dressing and toss.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix all except oranges and Cool Whip with 2 1/2 cups water. Boil until thick.
Cool and add oranges and Cool Whip.
Optional: cottage cheese and pineapple.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: First, drain the pineapple very well.
Then in a large mixing bowl, mix all of the above ingredients.
Mix well.
Lime Jell-O may be used to change the flavor.
It may also be made with sugar-free Jell-O and reduced calorie Cool Whip to make it a diet salad.

title: boiled chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up the chicken into serving pieces and stew in 3 quarts of salted water.
When chicken is tender, add the other ingredients. Then gradually add Bott Boi to boiling broth.
Cover and boil for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley and hard cooked eggs and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour in graham cracker or pie crust shell.
Refrigerate.

title: stir-fry rice and beef
directions: Cut meat into thin strips about 1-inch long.
Cut onion into wedges and pepper into thin strips.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok over high heat about 5 minutes.
Remove from wok.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok over medium-high heat.
Add onion and pepper and stir-fry until vegetables are tender and crisp, about 2 minutes.
Add meat and rice to vegetables.
Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over rice, meat and vegetables.
Serve warm.
Serves 5 to 8.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into well greased and floured tube pan.
Place apples in pan.
Cover with remaining batter.
Top with some apples.
Bake 1 1/4 hour at 350°, cool 20 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: The avocado is peeled and thoroughly mashed; the tomato is peeled, then mashed. The onion is minced as finely as possible. This is all mixed together thoroughly with lemon juice (better, lime juice), a little olive oil, salt and pepper, and the shallot top minced to the nth degree. Place mixture in a bowl, surrounded by tostados or Fritos and allow your guest to dip and dip again.

title: toast framed egg
directions: Cut 3-inch diameter circle in toast.
Place toast on microwave-safe plate.
Break egg into hole.
Pierce yolk with fork. Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook, covered, on Roast or Slo cook for 1 minute or until egg is cooked as desired.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter over low heat. Stir constantly. Pour in noodles.
Stir until noodles are coated well.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: pudding pie
directions: Beat pudding and milk and set aside.
Beat (room temperature) cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Beat and pour cream cheese mixture into prepared cooked regular pie shells or graham cracker shells, then add pudding on top.
Makes 2 large pies or 3 small.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Blend butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually add eggs and lemon extract and beat until blended.
Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Add nuts and raisins to flour.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate on chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Leave in pan; slice into 24 squares.
Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in pan.
Boil for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Pour over presliced cake, making sure syrup goes between slices.

title: curry coconut chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°, grease jelly roll pan.
Mix milk and egg in bowl, mix coconut and curry in shallow dish.
Dip chicken into milk mixture, then coat with coconut mixture.
Place in pan.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes, turn chicken.
Bake uncovered 5-8 minutes longer, until no longer pink in the center.
Serve chicken with Honey Mustard Sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put vegetables in colander and pour boiling water over top. Toss lightly the chicken, onion rings (save some for top) and vegetables.
Put in casserole.
Pour soup and milk over top. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Put onions on top and return to oven for 5 minutes more.

title: zucchini mix
directions: Saute zucchini, onions and sausage.
Pour tomato sauce over. Mix and heat together.

title: deep dish peach pie
directions: Peel and pit peaches; cut into 3/4-inch thick slices (you should have 5 to 6 cups).
In a small bowl, combine granulated sugar and salt.
Arrange a layer of peach slices in an 8-inch square baking pan and sprinkle with some of the sugar mixture. Repeat layers until all peaches and sugar mixture are used. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Using a pastry blender of 2 knives, cut butter into flour mixture until particles are about the size of peas.
Mix in nuts. Sprinkle crumb mixture evenly over peaches.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until topping is browned.
Serve warm or refrigerate and serve cold.
Top each portion with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts; pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; let cool.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Stir cheese to soften.
Fold in whipped cream, then add the remaining ingredients.
Freeze until firm.
Serve in a lettuce cup. A nice salad for a ladies' luncheon.
Serves 10.

title: bucket cake
directions: Cool cake and cut into 2-inch squares.
Layer as follows in 5-quart ice cream bucket:
cake, pudding (1 flavor), 1 tub Cool Whip, 5th Avenue crumbs, cake, pudding (other flavor), 1 tub Cool Whip and 5th Avenue crumbs.

title: breakfast special
directions: In a heavy 10-inch skillet, arrange bacon slices.
Cook until bacon is crisp.
Remove skillet from heat.
Remove and crumble the bacon.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add potatoes to skillet.
Sprinkle with dash of salt and pepper.
Return to stove and stir-fry until potatoes are light brown.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Roll the dried beef in the breasts, then wrap the bacon slices around them and secure with a toothpick.
Mix the sour cream and soups together.
Place the breasts into a greased casserole dish. Pour the mixture over all and bake at 350° for about 2 hours. Serve with rice. This is a costly recipe but nice for special occasions.

title: lemon frosted mincemeat squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Add dry ingredients and water.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts, raisins and mincemeat. Spread thin in 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chow chow
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions and slice.
Chop pepper and mix all ingredients together in a large 7-quart canner.
Cook over low heat until this mixture thickens, about 3 hours.
Put in jars and seal.
Good served with beans and other vegetables.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased casserole. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: venison roast(an old family recipe; great for tougher cuts)
directions: Place meat in covered glass or plastic container.
Cover with red wine and marinate overnight.
Drain and place in crock-pot. Lay strips of bacon over meat and sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cook on low for 8 hours.
Remove meat and keep warm.
Pour juice into measuring cup; skim fat and add water or beef broth to make 2 cups.
Put reserved fat or 3 tablespoons butter into saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in 3 tablespoons flour and cook briefly.
Add reserved meat drippings all at once and stir over heat until thickened.
Add mushrooms.
Serve roast sliced and topped with gravy, with noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together chilies, sour cream and soup; cream together. Warm tortillas in microwave until soft.
Spoon some chili mixture and chicken pieces in tortillas.
Roll up and place in baking dish.
Top with remaining chili mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
When melted, add peanut butter.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal.
Spoon on cookie sheet or waxed paper and let cool.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples; bring to a boil.
Boil until thick.
Slice enough apples to fill 7 quarts.
Pour mixture over apples.
Seal jars and process in open canner for 20 minutes.

title: spice cookies
directions: Into large bowl, measure sugar and remaining ingredients, except the currants.
With mixer at medium speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl.
Stir in currants. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and serve in a chafing dish over low heat with choice of crackers. Can also be served chilled.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: delicious cinnamon buns
directions: Melt mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.
Roll dough and coat with softened butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut approximately one-inch thick.
Place into pan with topping.
Let rise again until double (approximately 45 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out onto a tray and let rest for a minute before removing pan.

title: bar cheese
directions: Melt cheese. Add horseradish (not horseradish sauce).
Add Tabasco sauce.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine over low heat for approximately 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Boil chicken in approximately 6 cups of water.
Debone when cooked.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth; do not drain.
Add Velveeta and stir until melted, adding onion mixture, Ro-Tel and chicken.
May put in oven to finish heating completely.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and water until berries pop.
Add sugar and Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
When cool and mixture begins to thicken, stir in pineapple, grapes and nuts.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart ring mold and refrigerate.
Garnish with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, onions, bell pepper, brown sugar and vinegar.
Cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Mix 1/2 of sauce mixture with hamburger.
Pour half on top.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in three (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Using mixer, whip cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Serve chilled with your favorite topping.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into well-greased 9x13 inch baking dish.
Bake 45-60 minutes or until center is firm.

title: miss dora's monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cream butter and gradually add sugars, beating well. Add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla, and corn syrup; beat well. Mix in oats, baking soda, and salt, stirring well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop dough by 1/4 cupful 4 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12-15 minutes. Center of cookies will be slightly soft. Cool slightly on sheets, remove to wire racks and cool completely.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° until done.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Blend margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in chopped candy bars and dry ingredients until well blended.
Chill 30 minutes.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool. Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: snackin' granola bars
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly onto well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store, tightly covered, in cool, dry place.

title: french custards
directions: In heavy frying pan, heat 1 cup sugar.
Do not stir or touch until brown.
Turn off stove and mix until melted.
Pour into 2-quart deep dish casserole; set aside.
Heat milk in saucepan on low.
In another bowl beat eggs with 1/2 cup sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add to milk gradually; mix.
Pour over caramel in casserole.
Place in large pan filled with water and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: Heat the butter in large skillet.
Saute the zucchini, garlic and onion until tender. Add tomatoes, seasonings and wine. Reduce heat.
Simmer slowly until liquid is completely reduced. Serve as side dish or good over rice.

title: wassail
directions: In crock-pot or large kettle, combine juices, sugar and spices. Take whole orange stud with whole cloves.
Drop into juices. Simmer one hour on high, then several hours on low.
Serve warm.
A holiday favorite.

title: surprise muffins(makes 12 medium muffins)
directions: In large bowl, beat egg slightly with fork.
Stir in milk and cooking oil.
In separate bowl, sift together dry ingredients. Add to large bowl.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy; do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups half full of batter.
Drop a scant teaspoon of jelly on center of batter.
Add more batter to fill the cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Place can of milk in freezer until frosty on outside of can. Drain pineapple into small saucepan and heat juice.
Combine Jell-O and cream cheese with warm juice.
Beat milk until stiff; fold in pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in juice mixture. Place nuts on top.

title: grandma's wilted lettuce salad
directions: Fry the bacon with the pepper and garlic salt until crisp. Remove the bacon and break into small pieces.
Return to grease. Place lettuce in a large bowl.
Add warm bacon and grease and onions.
Toss together and serve immediately.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in top of double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Stir and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix last three ingredients and pour over salad.
Mix well and chill.
(I add shredded carrots for color.)

title: pecan tassies
directions: Let one 3 ounce package cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften; blend together.
Stir in 1 cup sifted all-purpose flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape in 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Press dough against bottom and sides.
Beat together egg, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and salt just until smooth.
Divide 1/3 cup coarsely broken pecans among tarts.
Add egg mixture.
Top with 1/3 cup coarsely broken pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.
Remove from pans.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mushroom-stuffed beef roll
directions: Have the meat cutter butterfly the meat when you buy it.

title: giant stuffed shells
directions: In skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic until meat is crumbly.
Drain excess fat.
Cool.
Stir in shredded cheese, parsley, crumbs, egg and season to taste with salt and pepper. Cook shells in salted water until almost tender (approximately 15 minutes); drain.
Use meat mixture to stuff shells.
Make a layer with 1 cup of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place stuffed shells on top of sauce side by side in single layer. Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until stems are almost tender; 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole. Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in a large skillet. Add onions and saute until soft (20 minutes).
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter and toss with crackers.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate. Stir flour into sauteed onions; cook 1 minute.
Stir in chicken broth and cook until thickened and creamy (2 minutes).
Remove from heat. Whisk together egg yolks and sour cream.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper. Add to onions and mix.
Pour onion mixture into pie plate. Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and put in greased angel food cake pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef; drain grease off. Add spaghetti sauce to ground beef and mix well. Set aside. Cook noodles in 2 quarts of boiling water for 6 minutes. Drain noodles and rinse well. Set aside. Combine beaten egg, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes. Set aside. Spray inside of crock-pot with cooking spray. Put layer of noodles in the bottom of crock-pot. Spread spaghetti sauce and hamburger over noodles. Top with 1/4 cup of shredded Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses. Add a layer of noodles. Repeat all the steps until you reach the top of the crock-pot. The top layer will be the hamburger layer. Cook the lasagna 1 hour on high. Turn temperature to low and cook for 3 hours more. Add remaining cheese 1 hour before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on the box.
Dice tomatoes, onions, cucumbers and green peppers and mix with drained pasta. Add 3/4 jar of salad dressing.
Mix Italian dressing according to the directions and pour over salad.
Chill overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Tear beef into small pieces in a large bowl.
Add all the ingredients to beef with your hands.
Form into a ball.
Chill at least a couple of hours.

title: grandma's raisin cookies
directions: Bring water and raisins to boil in saucepan.
Cook 3 minutes. Cool.
Do not drain.
Cream shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until set, but not hard.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs with mixer.
Beat in sugar until light. Sift dry ingredients and add to oil mixture, beat well.
Remove beaters and stir in apples by hand.
Spread batter in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle lemon juice over batter. Do not stir in.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Cool and frost with frosting.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir green beans and soup together in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening.
Add yeast water.
The dough will be rather sticky.
Use a wooden spoon to mix.
Keep stirring until the dough is elastic like strands when you pull the dough from the bowl. Place the dough in a greased bowl and cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate immediately.
The next day, place the dough on a well floured board.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
Place them on a greased pan.
Cover with a cloth and let rise until doubled in size.
You may brush with margarine before or after baking. Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, shortening, butter, vanilla and 1/2 of the cake mix until smooth.
Then stir in remaining cake mix until smooth.
Roll dough out and cut in shape desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Poke fork holes in when fresh out of oven. Cool.
Put on ice cream between layers and freeze.

title: pear romaine salad
directions: Wash, dry and slice romaine lettuce into long, thin strips. Mix balsamic vinegar and oil pour on lettuce.
Toss well.
Put on salad plates.
Top with bleu cheese crumbles.
Core pear and cut into slices.
Saut in butter until brown.
Put on top of lettuce and top with pecan halves.
Serves 2.

title: clark bar pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in the milk.
Cool.
Crush candy bars.
Stir into marshmallow mixture; add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add bananas and pecans.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 8 x 13 bowl and put in refrigerator until set.
Spread on sour cream.
Pour on remaining Jell-O mixture on top.
Place in refrigerator until entire mixture sets.

title: holiday fruit balls
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
Mix together remaining ingredients except coconut.
Pour milk over mixture.
Stir together until well mixed. Form into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in coconut.
Pack in airtight container.
Yield: 200 balls.

title: cold taco snack
directions: First mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
On 12-inch plate, spread cream cheese and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with onion, shredded lettuce, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Top with taco sauce.
The taco chips are used to dip into the mixture.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole dish 30 minutes at 350°.
Add a little grated cheese over top.

title: egg drop soup
directions: To Microwave:
In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, stir together broth, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth; stir in ham, snow peas and onions.
Cover with lid; microwave on High 10 minutes or until boiling, stirring twice during cooking. With fork, stir broth in swirling motion.
Without stirring, slowly pour eggs into swirling broth; then stir just until eggs are set in long strands.

title: microwave homemade pie shell
directions: Place flour and salt in small bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening until mixture resembles small peas. Sprinkle water over mixture.
Stir with fork to form a ball.
Roll out on
floured pastry board with rolling pin to about 12-inch circle.
Fit into glass 9-inch pie plate.
Trim and flute edge. Prick pastry with fork.
Cook on High for 6 to 7 minutes.
Pastry is done when it looks dry and blistered and is not doughy.
Cool; add filling.

title: jelly glaze for baked ham
directions: Mix together; baste ham until brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Add all ingredients, leaving the Doritos for last.
Add Doritos right before serving.

title: quick ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in butter in large skillet until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon brand and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 30 minutes. Cool.
Chill.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Garnish with lemon as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: best apple crisp ever
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter 2 x 10 x 15-inch baking dish. Toss apples with lemon juice in large bowl.
Add 1 cup brown sugar and toss to coat.
Arrange apple mixture in even layer in prepared baking dish.
Mix remaining 1 cup brown sugar, oats, flour and cinnamon in large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over apples.
Bake about 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Cook apricots until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 to 45 minutes over low heat.

title: crock-pot taco soup
directions: Cook meat; drain. Add all ingredients to crock-pot (do not drain cans). Stir. Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours or low for 4 to 5 hours. Serve. Garnish with cheese and sour cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapples and add enough water to make two cups.
Heat this to boiling and then dissolve Jells in it, then add 1 cup cold water.
Let this set and start to jell in the refrigerator.
Fold in the can of whole cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Let it jell.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
Add cheese until melted. Mix in mayo.
Mix in bell pepper and pimiento.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, green onions (chopped) and chilies well.
Spread on flour tortillas; roll tortillas up.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 stuffing and butter together.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Bone and shred chicken.
Mix chicken and soup together. Pour over stuffing in pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread remaining stuffing over top.
Pour chicken broth over this and brown in oven at 375° to 400°.
Can be prepared the day before needed.

title: easy sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage and drain on paper towels.
Divide and spread evenly in the bottom of the pie shells.
Mix eggs, sour cream, mustard, milk, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour mixture over sausage in pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: wing dings
directions: Cut wings at joints.
Discard tips.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Marinate wings.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Turn often and baste.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In a large dishpan or plastic container, combine crackers, raisins, nuts and fruit.
Mix well.
Melt the marshmallows with the condensed milk in microwave in a large bowl.
Pour into dishpan with other ingredients. Mix well and add juice to mixture. Mixture needs to be moist enough to pack in a 13 x 9 x 2 cake pan.
Line pan with wax paper for easy removal.
Chill in refrigerator, then cut into 5 pieces the narrow way.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box in two 9-inch layers.
Cool and slice each layer into two layers.
Mix sugar and sour cream together.
Add 1 1/2 packages of coconut to sugar mixture.
Place filling between layers and sprinkle with remainder.
Let stand overnight or several hours before serving.
This freezes well. Keep stored in refrigerator.
Stays moist a long time.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain, reserving water.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth. Sift flour, salt, soda and spices; mix with oatmeal.
Add and cream raisin liquid.
Add dates and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and use 2 tablespoons for each cup of hot water.

title: liver arlesienne(a good dish for families where not all members like liver.)
directions: *If using beef liver, place liver in a flat dish and cover with milk.
Let sit 3 or more hours.
This softens the flavor of the liver.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour all fruit, except mandarin oranges, in large bowl with their juices.
Drain oranges, then add them to the fruit mixture. Add dry pudding and drink powder.
Stir until thoroughly mixed. Refrigerate.

title: curry apples
directions: Core apples and slice.
Dip apple in pie plate with lemon and water.
Drain.
Spread the topping on the apples and sprinkle with curry.
Topping will accommodate 2 apples.

title: aunt neva's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size bowl.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown. Yield: 10 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water; drain.
Season with pepper, margarine and 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Add soup, sour cream and pimento.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake in a casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dilled barbecue turkey
directions: Place turkey in a glass baking dish.
In a small bowl combine all remaining ingredients; spread over turkey.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove turkey, reserve marinade.
Grill turkey, covered, over medium-hot coals, basting often with marinade, for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until juices run clear or internal temperature reaches 170°.

title: gumdrop popcorn(popcorn cake)
directions: Mix margarine, marshmallows, salt and vanilla in saucepan over low heat.
In a bowl mix popcorn with gumdrops.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn mixture.
Mix together.
Wet hands with cold water and shape into balls.
May also be pushed down into a cake pan or bread pan.

title: aunt bee's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together. Add eggs, vanilla, pound cake mix and pecans. Mix well. Add confectioners sugar. Mix. Batter will be thick. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: virgie's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Place pecans on bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Pour on mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
The nuts rise to the top, which will be crusty. A knife inserted in will come out clean.

title: frozen oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble cookies in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter; pour over cookie crumbs and press down. Freeze for 15 minutes.

title: chinese fans
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Line 2 nonstick baking sheets with baking mats.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a bowl, use an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment.
Cream the butter and 3/4 cup sugar until the mixture is light & fluffy.
Add the vanilla, milk, egg and lemon zest. Slowly add dry ingredients.
When well mixed, remove the dough from the bowl.
Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Row out each piece of dough between 2 pieces of plastic wrap to form a rough circle 8 inches across and a 1/4 inch thick.
Peel off the top piece of plastic wrap, and use a pastry wheel to cut the circle into 6 equal wedges.
Using the back of a knife, mark each cookie with 3 or 4 lines radiating from the point of the triangle. Brush with egg white.
Sprinkle each group of wedges with 1 Tbsp. sugar.
Transfer to cookie sheets.
Bake until crisp and golden brown, 10-12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: italian chicken(pastor chris' favorite)
directions: Pour Italian dressing mix into a plastic bag and take each piece of chicken and coat with dressing.
Cook or bake in a glass dish for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: party punch
directions: Make a syrup of 6 cups sugar and 4 cups water.
While hot, add jello.
When cool, add lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice, 1 gallon water and almond.

title: one dish chicken meal
directions: Cut up chicken.
Slice bell pepper, onions and potatoes in large pieces and place in large deep dish pan.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over this.
Bake at 350° at least 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bread and salad and you have a great meal.

title: hot spiced tea(christmas gift)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in individual small jars (baby food jars or 1/2 pint jars).
Decorate with ribbons and holly.
Great gifts for good friends.

title: springerle
directions: Beat eggs 1/2 hour.
Gradually add powdered sugar until mixed (5 or 10
minutes).
Add anise oil, then add flour, salt and baking powder by
folding
in
with
a
spoon.
Roll
out 1/4-inch thick
and	press
design
with a springerle board or springerle rolling
pin.
Cut	apart and let set out overnight on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 or 20 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients.
