Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until toothpick placed in center remains clean.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cherry cheese cupcakes
directions: Whip cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Place one wafer in a cupcake paper.
Fill it with 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown onion and pepper in teaspoon oil.
Mix soup, Ro-Tel, chili powder and garlic salt in a medium sized pan and heat. Place Doritos on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour broth from chicken on crushed Doritos (enough to cover 1/2 of the Doritos). Place chicken pieces on top of Doritos and pour soup mixture on top of chicken.
Put onion and pepper on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and place Velveeta on top. Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cream well and then add other ingredients and mix.
Make in small balls and mash flat.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
You can add chopped pecans or chocolate.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, milk and melted shortening.
Stir into dry mixture and add corn. Drop from tablespoon into about 1/2-inch of hot oil in skillet. Drain on paper towels.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Simmer pork steaks until tender.
Drain can of sauerkraut. Cook noodles as directed.

title: redfish supreme
directions: Sprinkle onions on fillets.
Sprinkle margarine on fillets. Sprinkle lemon juice on fillets.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce on fillets.
Pour tomatoes over fillets.
Cover with parsley.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Great served over a bed of rice, using sauce cooked in the pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosted butterscotch bars
directions: Let ice cream melt at room temperature.

title: dena's lemon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease loaf pan. Combine butter and sugar. Mix well. Add eggs, lemon peel, extract and milk. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Stir until just moistened. Fold in nuts. Pour into pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all items together.
If too dry, add a little condensed milk.
Shape into cake and put into refrigerator.
I use cracker and raisin boxes to store.
To mix a large amount, increase each item accordingly.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix and pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
About 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place chicken into a deep dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, wine and margarine in a small bowl.
Lay the 8 slices over the chicken; pour mixture over the cheese.
Top with stuffing mix. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs slightly and combine with sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Slowly add scalded milk; mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes.

title: pickle fiddleheads
directions: Cook the vinegar, water and pickle salt for 3 to 5 minutes. Pour over fiddleheads that are already in canning jars.
Once this is done, place each amount of spice in each jar.
Seal jars; cook for 5 minutes in canner.

title: baked turkey tetrazzini
directions: Arrange spaghetti in a large greased baking dish.
Drain mushrooms and reserve broth.
Top spaghetti with turkey and mushrooms.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil onion and sliced zucchini together for 5 minutes.
Stir together cream of chicken soup, sour cream and grated carrots. Stir onion and zucchini in with this also (after boiling).
Pour this vegetable mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with corn chips or Tostados.
To keep fresh, place avocado seed in center of guacamole.

title: tooter's taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain; add seasoning mix and water.
Return to boil; reduce heat to simmer for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Layer on toppings; cut into squares.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Break bread in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Mix eggs and all other ingredients and pour over bread.
Cover tightly with foil.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake covered at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes, then cut into squares and serve.
Fresh fruit goes well with this dish.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Place on a wire rack.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift.
Add egg, milk, sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients and just enough flour so doesn't stick.
Chill.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Blend bananas well in processor or blender.
Add pineapple and blend.
Add remaining ingredients (except 7-Up).
Blend and freeze in individual serving containers.
(2 lb. size butter bowls makes 4 servings).
Set out 15-30 minutes prior to serving.
Then pour some of the 7-Up over tops.
Will make a mush-ice consistency.

title: oriental veal casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Roll meat in flour; brown in hot oil over medium heat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, 1 3/4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 2 hours, covered, in a 300° oven, then 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil together first five items.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper to cool or spread on pan to harden.

title: crab meat stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Dry thoroughly.
Bake at 325° until tender. Cut baked potatoes lengthwise.
Scoop out potato and place in large bowl.
Add butter, milk, salt, pepper, onion and cheese. Whip.
Mix in crab meat.
Re-fill potato shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Re-heat in very hot oven for 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Scald milk with cinnamon, remove cinnamon and add butter and sugar; stirring well.
Add slowly to beaten eggs, mix well.
Add rice and raisins.
Turn into buttered baking dish and bake in slow oven (300°) for 45 minutes or until brown.
Yields 6 portions.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove the stems.
Place mushroom caps on a cookie sheet.
Chop stems in a food processor until fine.
Saute margarine, finely chopped garlic and 2 cups bread crumbs.
Add chopped mushroom stems to sauteed mixture.
Cool until thickened. Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil peas, add a little salt and drain.
Mix all; set overnight and add more dressing in the morning.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook until tender the potatoes and onion in enough salted water to cover.
Add milk and pepper; heat thoroughly.
In the meantime, in small skillet, heat flour until browned.
Melt in butter.
Stir browned flour slowly into soup and simmer for a few minutes, adding parsley and chopped eggs.

title: chicken & dumplings
directions: Bring water, chicken, mushroom soup, pepper, and bouillon to boil, stirring often.
Separate biscuits in half.
Drop 1 at a time into boiling mixture.
Stir gently.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer.
Stirring occasionally 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook 25 minutes.

title: baked fresh tuna
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rub tuna steaks with oil; season lightly with pepper.
In skillet, saute onion in remaining oil until it is limp.
Add chopped tomatoes and vermouth; cook briefly.
Place steaks in a shallow pan.
Pour on onion-tomato mixture.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, depending on thickness.
Sprinkle with basil.
Serves 4.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Make cream puff dough.	Bake in a 10 x 15 greased pan for 15 to 20 minutes; cool.

title: colonial innkeepers pie
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Add 2/3 cup sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla; set aside.
Mix and sift flour, 3/4 cups sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Beat two minutes. Add egg; beat two minutes more.
Pour batter into unbaked pie shell. Stir chocolate sauce and pour carefully over batter.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken 'n' rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, milk and rice and pour in dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Sprinkle dry onion mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Add 1 1/2 or 2 cups of crushed crackers (Waverly wafers or Ritz), and pour over vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Mix sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Cook to form a soft ball in cold water.
Add marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Beat until dissolved, then add pecans.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: peach crepes
directions: Put the flour into mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center of the flour and the egg.
While whisking, pour in the nondairy creamer and then the skim milk.
Continue to whisk until the batter is smooth and free of lumps, then whisk in the nutmeg and vanilla. Cover the batter and set it aside for 30 minutes.

title: oriental cashew crunch party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal, chow mein noodles and cashews in a 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
Combine oil, soy sauce, garlic and onion powders in a bowl.
Pour quickly over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes; cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 10 cups.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Cook ground meat (stirring so it doesn't stick together) with onion and garlic, until it is just done.
Mix with all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, until it's bubbly hot.
Be sure tamales and hominy are drained well.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add garlic, parsley and oregano; saute for 1 minute on medium high heat.
Add shrimp; lower heat to medium.
Cook shrimp until they turn pink.
One minute before serving, add vermouth.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: deviled crab
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Stir in flour and add next five ingredients.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add crab meat and eggs.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.
Yields 6 ramekins.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt
butter in a 9-inch baking dish.
Mix together the flour, sugar
and	milk and pour over the melted butter.
Pour peaches on top
of
batter.
Bake
at
400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fried turkey(use 2 or 3 frozen, 12-14 pound, whole turkeys.)
directions: Mix the marinate in a large cooler.
Two to three turkeys will fit in a large cooler.
Marinate for at least 3 days (5 days isn't too long) turning birds at least once daily from back to breast and mixing marinating ingredients each time.
Birds must be kept cold during the marinating process.
The day before or the day of the cooking, inject extra Louisiana hot sauce into the breast and thighs with a hypodermic needle, if desired.

title: honey cookies(real good)
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Combine all ingredients and drop on cookie sheet.
Press down with spoon.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 8 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until tender; add milk. Melt butter in saucepan; add flour.
Cook, stirring over low heat 3 minutes to make thick sauce.
Add to soup.
Stir constantly until hot and slightly thick.
Season to taste with thyme, celery salt, salt and pepper.

title: beef chili
directions: Heat oil in deep, large skillet over medium heat for 5 minutes.

title: easy chicken delight
directions: Place chicken pieces in pan that has been greased with vegetable oil.
Season with spices (pepper, Season-All, garlic powder and salt to taste) over front and back side.
Cover chicken with celery and onion; add water.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and brown off about 20 minutes at 250°.
Ready to serve.

title: christmas egg nog
directions: Blend egg yolks with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk, a little at a time, to ensure sugar dissolving.
Add nutmeg to taste. Add whiskey, about 1/2 bottle (more, if desired).
Blend and set aside. Whip the cream until stiff.
Whip egg whites with 1 tablespoon sugar until stiff.
Fold whipped cream and egg whites into egg yolk mixture. Serve in punch bowl decorated with nutmeg and plastic holly, if desired.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook chuck roast, rump or etc. until tender.
Tear meat into bite size pieces, then add to sauce. Simmer a few minutes.
Serve on buns.
You can freeze the sauce and add meat when needed.

title: trout with almonds
directions: Clean, wash and scale trout.
Dry thoroughly and roll lightly in flour.
Melt the butter in a frying pan.
When it is hot, but not brown, put in trout.
Cook over low heat 5 to 7 minutes; turn carefully and cook on other side for the same length of time. When golden brown, salt and pepper them and lay them carefully on a heated serving platter.
Add cream to the butter remaining in pan; mix rapidly and add almonds.
Stir carefully so that the almonds will not be broken and heat again just to the boiling point.
Do not boil sauce.
Spoon sauce over trout; add thin rounds of lemon and serve immediately.

title: fat-free cheese dip
directions: Melt ingredients in crock-pot and serve with chips.
Also, good on baked potatoes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Add cheese between layers of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over refried beans.
Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line Pyrex dish with chipped beef; wrap each half of chicken breast in bacon and place in dish lined with chipped beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together; cover chicken with mixture. Bake for 1 hour or until done at 325°.
Serve over rice cooked with chicken bouillon cubes.

title: herbed baby potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, toss potatoes in oil to coat each piece.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add fresh parsley to garnish.

title: pear cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar over pears and let set one hour.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix together and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: mae's french dressing
directions: Pour into empty dressing bottle.
Add clove garlic and shake well.
Let stand for 1 or 2 days.

title: baked fudge
directions: To beaten eggs, add dry ingredients, melted butter, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Set in pan of boiling water.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, until custard consistency.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 100 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut in chunks.
Set aside.
Cook spaghetti.
Saute onions and bell pepper in oil.
Add the 3 soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir in Cheddar soup, Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese, pimentos and black olives.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese and almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly and light brown.

title: savory rice
directions: Bring water and bouillon to boil.
Add rice; cover and cook according to package directions.
Dice peppers, celery and onions. Add them to hot, cooked rice and mix together.
In another bowl, mix the oil, soy sauce and parsley with black pepper to taste. Add this to the rice mixture, stirring well.
Place in serving bowl.
Refrigerate several hours and serve cold.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake 1 hour at 325° in bread pan (greased) or 30 minutes in muffin tins.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix all together and simmer 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: bacon-wrapped hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Shape mixture into 6 or 7 patties, each about 3/4-inch thick.
Crisscross 2 half slices bacon on each patty, tucking ends under.
Place patties on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Cook under cover in 350° oven 50 minutes. Makes 6 or 7 servings.

title: polynesian meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into meat balls (about teaspoon size). Brown in pan. Drain on paper towels.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale and water, together to form a punch syrup. When mixing punch in punch bowl, use 1 part punch to 1 part ginger ale and 1 part cold water. Use an ice mold in the punch bowl or serve over ice.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: artichoke hearts appetizers
directions: Drain and rinse artichoke hearts.
Dice into small pieces. Mix together all ingredients. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Cool and cut into small squares.
Serve with Italian bread or crackers.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Cover and chill several hours until firm.
Shape into a ball and roll in minced parsley or line a decorative mold with plastic wrap.
Pack spread into mold and chill.
Serve with wheat or sesame crackers or Melba toast.

title: roman roll-ups
directions: Have kids shred the chicken into thin pieces and set aside in a small bowl.

title: layer chocolate dessert
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: turkey tetrazzini(serves 12)
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth until tender.
Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in the butter. Drain noodles and mix together all ingredients leaving cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peppery vegetable dip
directions: In a small bowl, stir all ingredients; cover and refrigerate. Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery and squash.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, salt, cloves, cinnamon and sugar.
In a small bowl, beat eggs until fluffy; add to pumpkin mixture.
Then add evaporated milk and condensed milk.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes or until pie is "set" in center.

title: deviled peas in toast cups
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, peas and diced pimento.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove crusts from bread; press each slice into a 6-ounce custard cup. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove toast cups from custard cups; fill each with pea mixture.
Garnish with pimento as desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in bowl and serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix in order given. Cool in refrigerator until firm or about 2 hours before serving.

title: bean soup with frankfurters
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In a 3-quart saucepan bring beans, water and beef broth to a boil.
Cook for about 1 hour.
Add carrot and celery and continue cooking for 30 minutes.
In a separate frypan cook the bacon until transparent.
Add the onions; cook until golden.
Set aside. Mash soup through sieve or food mill.
Return to pan and add the bacon-onion mixture, salt and pepper.
Add frankfurters; reheat about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle soup with chopped parsley and serve.

title: pumpkin, raisin-nut bread(low calorie)
directions: Put all dry ingredients into mixer bowl; mix well.
Make hole in center and add next 4 ingredients; mix all well, scraping sides of bowl.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 medium loaf pans.

title: grape hamburger balls
directions: Mix hamburger and onion.
Add crushed saltine crackers.
Add egg and mix well.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add salt and pepper.
Form hamburger mixture into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn after 15 minutes baking.
Remove from sheet and drain.

title: mint brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of pan.
Mix brownies, syrup, water, oil, and egg with spoon about 50 strokes, until moist.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Place peppermint patties on top of brownies immediately after baking and return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes.
Spread over brownies.
Cool, then frost with Mint Fluff Frosting.
Keep any remaining brownies refrigerated.

title: canadian bacon waldorf salad
directions: Whisk sour cream, mayonnaise, juice concentrate, lemon juice and ginger in a large bowl.
Stir in apple, bacon, celery, dates and pecans.
Add sweet potatoes.
Serve over lettuce.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make crust in spring-form pan.

title: mom-in-laws bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not peel cucumbers; slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and salt.
Cover with cracked ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours and then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in pot and heat to boiling.
Add the cucumber mixture and bring to boil again.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.

title: light bread pudding with chocolate sauce
directions: Generously butter a 6 to 8-cup round souffle dish and set aside.
Spread bread slices with remaining butter on top and place slices in dish.
In a bowl beat eggs and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour mixture carefully through a strainer into pan with bread.
(Bread will float to the top.)
Put dish in a larger pan.
Add enough hot water to the larger pan to come halfway up side of baking dish.
Place in the center of a preheated 350° oven.
Lower heat to 325° for 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Sprinkle remaining sugar over top of pudding.
Broil 2 to 4 inches from preheated broiler until sugar melts and edges of bread turn golden brown.
Serve warm or at room temperature with Chocolate Sauce.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice apples in a 9-inch pie plate or dish.
Put sugar over apples.
Mix all remaining ingredients and spread over top of apples.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: monkey bread #2
directions: Cut each roll into quarters; place in large mixing bowl.
Add confectioners sugar and cinnamon to bowl; shake to cover all roll pieces.
Drop coated pieces into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Melt butter; add brown sugar to melted butter.
Pour this mixture over contents of pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and then turn over onto plate.
Eat with fingers.

title: hearty fare cheese chilies cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Whisk together eggs, yogurt and butter in medium bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix until just well blended. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch heavy skillet and bake 40 minutes or until well done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients in boiler.
Stir until boiling (3 minutes).
Add Jell-O.
Arrange fresh strawberries in bottom of pie shells.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer until thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: mom mom's lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with egg yolks (save egg whites for meringue). Squeeze juice from lemons and add to mixture; add vanilla and mix until thick. Pour in crust. Beat egg whites with sugar. Spread on pie and bake until lightly brown. When cool, refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: mystery pie
directions: Crush the crackers with rolling pin.
Mix with baking powder and chopped walnuts. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating constantly. Beat in vanilla. Fold cracker mixture into beaten egg mixture.

Spread in a 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cool thoroughly. Whip the cream and add confectioners sugar or spread Cool Whip over pie and top with shaved chocolate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Fill crust with peeled and sliced apples.
Cover with sugar, allspice and flour mixture.
Slice oleo and place over this layer. Cover with top crust.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: jumping jack
directions: Saute onion and celery in bacon fat in large saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: broil-bake crispy chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry and cut off fatty skin.
Sprinkle lightly on both sides with 3 spices.
Arrange, skin side down, on rack in a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 6 inches below heat until lightly browned (about 10 minutes).
Remove pan from oven.
Re-set oven to 500°.
Turn chicken over.
Pour boiling water into pan under chicken to depth of 1/2 inch.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until meat near bone is no longer pink.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake per box directions and cut into 1-inch cubes. Prepare pudding per box directions.
Layer half of ingredients in punch bowl: cake, pudding, pineapple, pie filling and Cool Whip, and then repeat.
Top with fresh fruit, if desired.
Then refrigerate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put in crock-pot and simmer all day or cook in regular boiler 2 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: chicken scuffle(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cut off bread crust and butter each side.
Place 6 slices in Pyrex dish (12 x 9-inch).
Place thick sliced cooked chicken on each slice, then top the chicken with a slice of cheese and the other slice of bread.
Whip the eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour the mixture over the sandwiches.
Cover with waxed paper and let stand overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with mushroom sauce.

title: cholesterol free mayonnaise
directions: In
a
blender combine egg whites and salt. Blend well. Add sugar
and
mustard and blend while slowly adding 1/2 cup oil and vinegar; add remaining 1/2 cup oil and lemon juice and blend until
thick.
Store
in
refrigerator.
Makes
about 1 pint. All liquids must be added very slowly.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Alternate chicken, pepper, mushrooms, tomato and onion on skewers.
Marinate in large baking pan for several hours in Kraft Zesty Italian dressing.
Baste with dressing while grilling. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 kabobs.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate the cream cheese, sour cream and 1/2 envelope taco seasoning mix.
Brown the ground beef.
Drain well. Add the other 1/2 of the taco seasoning and water.
Mix well and cool.
When cool, mix with tomatoes, onions and green pepper.
Put on top of cream cheese mix.
Top with cheese.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice, pepper and garlic powder. Place in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.
Baste occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and cook at 350° until brown and firm.

title: gourmet venison stew
directions: Trim fat from venison and cut into 1 to 2-inch cubes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix soda, salt and vanilla together and reserve.
Butter 2 cookie sheets (15 1/2 x 12-inch); keep warm.
Mix sugar, water and Karo in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to 240°.
Stir in butter and peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 300°.
Immediately remove from heat and stir in soda mixture.
Pour 1/2 of candy mixture onto each cookie sheet and quickly spread about 1/4-inch thick.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes on High, stirring well after 4 minutes. Stir in oleo and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes longer on High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour into lightly greased baking sheet (use Pam).
Spread out thin. (I use aluminum pie pans.)
When cool, break into small pieces. Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound of candy.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix melted margarine, sugar, vanilla, salt and lemon flavoring together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Dissolve soda in sour cream; add to mixture.
Fold in 3 cups plain flour, chopped nuts and strawberry jam.
Mix well and pour into 2 large or 4 small well-greased pans.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
In separate bowl, stir together the flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture; beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: chicken and brown rice pilaf
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken breasts and cook until brown. Remove chicken and add chicken broth and water. Bring to a boil. Stir in mushrooms, onion, peas and rice. Top with chicken; cover. Cook on low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Let stand 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: tortellini party snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Deep fry cheese tortellini at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 minutes.
(Do small amounts at a time if using small fryer.)
Place on paper towels to drain.
In large bowl, mix dill weed, oil and dressing mix.
Add tortellini to dill mixture.
Stir gently to coat.

Using a slotted spoon, spread tortellini on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes, stirring halfway through baking time. Spread out on paper towels and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Recipe can be doubled easily.

title: brook trout in bacon
directions: Clean and wash trout.
Pat dry and rub inside with salt.
Wrap in bacon and fasten with wooden picks.
Place in hand broiler and cook over hot coals, turning several times, until bacon is crisp and fish is done.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Bring to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Cool 1 hour.
Spread on frozen ice cream and freeze.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: *Such as carrots, summer squash, celery, zucchini, cabbage and mushrooms.

title: mexicorn dip
directions: Mix everything together and chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and set aside.
Cook ground round, place on pepper towel to drain.
Combine all ingredients and put into baking pan in which you have already sprinkled a thin layer of cornmeal and slightly browned.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until done.

title: ham and turkey sandwich
directions: Spread each half bun with dressing.
Place ham and turkey on bottom half of bun.
Top with cheese.
Cover with top half of bun. Wrap sandwich in aluminum foil.
Heat in 425° oven until meat is hot and cheese is melted, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square pan. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add liquids and mix until smooth. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: zippy mushroom appetizer
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Cover. Refrigerate 8 hours, stirring several times.
Drain and serve as appetizers.

title: rolled pork with three vegetables - yasai maki(servings:  2)
directions: Open pork and season with salt and pepper.
Put green beans, carrot and spring onions on the pork.
Roll the 3 vegetables in the pork.
Heat oil in a frying pan and fry from the edge of roll. Cover until brown.
Pour soy sauce in season.
Cut into 2 pieces; arrange on dish with cut side up.

title: chi chi's pico de gallo
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a 1-quart bowl.
Cover and let stand for 2 hours.
Serve as condiment for tacos, enchiladas, rice, tostada chips or refried beans.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together on wax paper. Beat butter and sugar together in medium size bowl until fluffy. Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cocoa.
Add milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients in 3 additions, beating well after each addition.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Brush a hot skillet with cooking oil and brown pork chops quickly.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion in same skillet over medium-high heat until it begins to brown, adding a little more oil if needed to keep from sticking.
Add sauerkraut to skillet and heat through, stirring.
Spread sauerkraut mixture on bottom of 8-inch square baking pan.
Top with half of apple slices. Place pork chops on top, season with salt and pepper to taste and top with remaining apple slices.
Deglaze skillet with wine and vinegar, stir in brown sugar and pour over pan of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 16 g, protein 19 g, fat 12 g, calories 255.

title: patty's world famous benedictine
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave on High for 20 minutes; set aside.
In a food processor, chop onion; set aside.
Peel half the cucumber and remove seeds.
Chop finely and drain in a colander to remove all liquid.

title: apple spice custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Prepare Ice Ring in advance.
In blender container, blend crushed pineapple and cream of coconut until smooth.
In large punch bowl, combine pineapple mixture with pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Add club soda and Ice Ring.
This recipe makes about 4 quarts or 36 (5 ounce) servings.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Hand beat eggs with small amount of milk.
Slice eggplant into thin slices.
Dip in egg batter and then in crumbs.
Saute in Crisco oil until browned and crispy looking.
Place one layer on bottom of a baking dish.
Spread tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Repeat layers until casserole is filled.
Pour leftover tomato liquid over top.
Sprinkle with more crumbs and cheese. Bake about 1 hour (surface will be bubbly) at 300°.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In 10-inch skillet cook the zucchini and onion in butter until tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture. Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 11-inch quiche pan or 10-inch pie pan.
Press dough over bottom and up sides to form crust. Spread with the mustard.
Pour vegetables evenly into crust.
Pour eggs and cheese over top. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken and yogurt
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add onion and wine.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or more.
Add yogurt.
Serve chicken and pour sauce over.
Serves 2.

title: shirley's spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Melt margarine. Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add margarine and lemon juice. Place drained spinach in shallow dish. Pour margarine and cream cheese mixture over spinach and serve. Great for dinner parties. Easy to prepare.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well, then chill dough.
Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen snappy cookies.

title: crab cheese dip
directions: Put garlic through garlic press; mix with ingredients.
Use enough mayonnaise or cream to moisten.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Line large baking pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Mix apricot preserves, red Russian dressing and onion soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Depending on your oven you can cut cooking time down or temperature to 350°.

title: 5 layer broccoli(side dish)
directions: Layer all ingredients in the order given.
Crumble the Ritz crackers.
Heat through at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Great side dish for a buffet or barbecue!

title: dessert flurries
directions: With large spoon, take 2 or more scoops of vanilla ice cream. Add Nerds, cookies or whatever and stir until mixed well.
Add whipped cream on top and serve.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar for 2 minutes.
Let cool and pour over mixed ingredients.
Let cool 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Fill with ice and blend until smooth.
Adults may add peach Schnapps.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes. Drop into buttered muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: beef-cabbage bake
directions: Cook rice in boiling water for 20 minutes, until the rice is tender.
Cook ground beef and onions until the onions are tender and the meat is no longer pink; drain off the fat.
Combine cooked and drained rice and ground meat mixture with Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Butter a 3-quart casserole.
Place 1/2 of the chopped cabbage for the first layer.
Pour 1/3 of the tomatoes over cabbage.
Next, place meat mixture and the rest of the cabbage.
Press down some and add the rest of the tomatoes.
You may sprinkle salt, pepper, Italian seasoning or basil if you desire.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: virginia's easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef in a 3 quart saucepan; drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except lasagna, for filling.
Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagna over sauce.
Lasagna will expand to fill empty spaces. Cover with about 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread 1/2 cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with layer of lasagna and remaining sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Remove foil; bake 10 minutes longer.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting for easier handling.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except croutons with 3/4 cup of butter.
Top with croutons and other 1/2 cup of butter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cranberry bread(2 loaves)
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: meringue torte
directions: Cream butter; beat in 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix and sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add flavoring.
Spread in two shallow cake pans.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add cream of tartar and beat in 1 cup sugar slowly.
Spread over cakes (leave 1-inch from edge of pan).
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or coconut.
Bake for 25 minutes at 250°, then 20 minutes longer at 350°.
Spread with whipped cream and crushed pineapple.

title: won ton
directions: Mix meat, shrimp, salt, soy sauce, wine and celery or water chestnuts.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of filling in center of wrapping. Fold wonton as directed on package.
Deep fry.
Serve hot.
Dip in sweet 'n sour sauce.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix corn and eggs.
Add crackers, onion (optional), salt, pepper and milk until creamy.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sassy beans
directions: Saute onions and garlic. Place in a bowl and mix in bacon or ham. Bake one hour at 350 degrees Makes 10-12 servings.

title: petersmarck glop
directions: Boil large pot of water and cook noodles approximately 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper.
Drain beef mixture and add mushroom soup, can of water, Worcestershire sauce, corn and some or all seasonings to taste.
Add cooked, drained noodles.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Let cheese melt and then serve.

title: chinese chews
directions: In a saucepan, melt the margarine until it is hot.
Add the other ingredients in order named, mixing well.
Pour batter into rectangular cake pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Spray electric grill or skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Preheat.
Cook chicken until done.
Tear chicken into stringy pieces using a fork.
Spread 1 to 2 Tbsp. salsa on a tortilla. Sprinkle with chicken, onion and cheese.
Top with a tortilla. Return to grill or skillet.
Cook until lightly browned on each side, turning once.
Repeat for additional quesadillas.
Cut into 4 pieces and serve while hot.

title: best peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, cocoa, syrup and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture begins to harden.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let harden before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk all at once.
Whisk until well blended. Add sour cream and Cool Whip, whisking until blended.
(If you want to spread Cool Whip over top of pudding, buy a larger container and keep some aside.)

title: prune cake
directions: Mix as you would any cake and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Mix salad dressing and sugar; pour over first mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: one-skillet spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Stir in uncooked spaghetti and the next 8 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and heat until melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate-cream cheese brownies
directions: Grease and lightly flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate and butter; cool.
Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat 4 eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla; gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Continue beating until thick and lemon colored.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture; blend well and stir in chocolate mixture and nuts.
Beat cheese and remaining sugar and vanilla.
Spread 1/2 chocolate in pan.
Pour cheese mixture over; top with remaining chocolate mixture and swirl to marble layer if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: carrot-pecan casserole
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of boiling water in a medium saucepan for 12 to 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain carrots and mash.
Stir in sugar and next 8 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: mincemeat hermits
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, well beaten eggs and milk and mix.
Mix together dry ingredients and add small amount to first mixture.
Add mincemeat and remaining flour.
Drop batter by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° until brown.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Break up crackers and place on cookie sheet close together.
Chop up nuts.
Cook butter, margarine and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Spread mixture over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 7 minutes at 325°. Place on wax paper to cool.

title: little indian corn cakes
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside. In separate bowl, combine corn, sugar, milk, eggs, onion and green pepper.
Stir dry ingredients into corn mixture.
Add Tabasco. Grease 8 muffin cups or 1 tray of 8 muffin cups; fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: called so good
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, salt and pepper; set aside.
Cook 1 cup macaroni; set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onions in bite size pieces. Mix in raisins and nuts; toss.

title: georgia grits(yankee style)
directions: Combine in a large pot the grits, salt and water.
Cook until grits are done; stir often.
Add butter or oleo, seasoned salt and cheese.
Remove from heat when cheese and butter are melted.
Add eggs.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 325° until well set. Serves 12 to 20.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together and put in the pie shell. Chill 4 to 6 hours, then serve.

title: chicken and broccoli divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and place in buttered baking dish.
Cover with chicken and soup mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over mixture and dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring the first three ingredients to a boil.
Add the mixture of the last three ingredients.
Boil until the tapioca is clear. Add more tapioca if needed to thicken.
I sometimes make a gallon of this and put into pint jars and seal.

title: orange angel delight
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add boiling water.
Add sugar and stir to dissolve. Add small can frozen orange juice (12 ounce can) and juice of lemon.
Whip pint of whipping cream until stiff.
Fold in mixture. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Alternate layers, beginning with cake. Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: stuff with rice
directions: In large pan, brown ground meat and onion.
Add green beans, tomatoes, soy sauce (until liquid looks brown) and water; bring to boil.
Add rice; reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook 20 minutes, until rice is done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Wash and dry corn.
Scrape off kernels then re-scrape with dull edge of knife.
Beat eggs and milk together; add corn, sugar, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 375° until pudding is just set, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and then combine together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes. Squares are done when knife comes out clean.
Allow to cool 1/2 hour before cutting.

title: barbara t's mock salmon mousse
directions: Mix flaked tuna, cream cheese, onion, mayo, lemon juice and Tabasco.
In saucepan, heat tomato soup with gelatin until dissolved.
Add tuna mixture.
Pour into greased mold and chill.

title: low-fat lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg whites and margarine together. Alternately add flour and sour cream to creamed mixture; blend until smooth. Add lemon and vanilla flavorings; mix well. Turn into tube pan sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: westhaven cake
directions: Mix dates, soda and water and let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add date mixture and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir together.
Sprinkle on top chocolate chips and nut meats.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken rice dish
directions: Fill soup cans with milk.
Stir good and let stand with rice about 5 minutes.
Place chicken on top.
Take margarine and put pieces on top of chicken.
Sprinkle on top onion soup mix.
Cover with foil or use covered roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
If you want it brown, take the cover off the last 5 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and a dash of celery seed.
Add onion rings, then beans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with half of crushed nacho chips.
Layer the chicken pieces over the chips.
Mix soups, chilies, cheeses and sour cream and spread over the chicken. Cover with remaining crushed nacho chips.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla; stir dry ingredients together and blend in.
Mix in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Mix together in a blender; add ice to desired thickness.

title: low-fat tangy topper
directions: Mix together and chill thoroughly.
Use as a salad dressing or substitute for sour cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and set aside. Cook onions in drippings.
Add seasoning and vinegar.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add beans and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: impossible brunch pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle meat, cheese, onions and mushrooms into plate.
Beat remaining ingredients in blender 15 seconds; pour over all.
Bake until golden brown or clean knife cut 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: egg sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix other ingredients.
Add sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dunn's divinity
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup, water and salt to 248°.
Cover and boil for 3 minutes.
Uncover and place thermometer in pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
When syrup is 248°, slowly pour about 1/2 of the syrup over the egg whites, beating constantly with the mixer.
Cook remaining syrup to 272°.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Put ingredients into blender.
Blend on medium speed until smooth.
Add more or less of above ingredients to taste.

title: chicken noel
directions: Place chicken in greased casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix remainder of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: pralines
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in pan.
Cook to 240° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir until it starts to lose gloss.
Drop in small portions on wax paper.
Work fast!

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Make batter with egg, flour, salt and water.
Salt and pepper the pork and coat with the batter.
Fry until brown.
Simmer with little water, covered, about 1 hour while making sauce.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake first 4 ingredients at 350° until done, about 30 minutes. When done, punch holes in top of cake while hot.
Punch with fork about 2-inches apart.
Mix together Eagle Brand and creme of coconut; pour over top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip, chopped pecans and toasted coconut.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cube chicken, mix with green chilies and soup.
Line a 13 x 9 inch pan with tortillas, cut in triangles.
Pour chicken mixture over tortillas.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish, skin side up.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika over chicken.

Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken. Sprinkle parsley flakes and paprika over top. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes to brown top. Can be served over rice or noodles with a green vegetable. Makes 3 servings.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cook meat, onion and pepper in skillet in hot oil until meat is browned.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss ingredients together and pour olive oil over to coat.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.
Stir potatoes every 15 minutes.

title: one pot spaghetti supper
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic in heavy deep pot.
Drain. Add seasonings.
Top with spaghetti.
Pour water and tomato juice over.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer and stir 15 minutes until spaghetti is tender and meat is done.
Add olives.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: nachos
directions: Break trout into small pieces.
For a smooth spread, put trout, cream cheese, dill, lemon juice, horseradish and salt in food processor and turn on/off several times.
For a chunkier spread, mix ingredients in a bowl until just blended.
Cover the bowl and refrigerate spread at least 2 hours until firm.
Sprinkle with dill before serving.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Cook
together	the brown sugar, pumpkin, spices, sugar and milk
over	low
heat
of double boiler until thickened to light custard
consistency.
Add	gelatin,
being
sure
it is dissolved.	Cool.
Beat
egg
whites with cream of tartar; add sugar slowly.
Fold
into cooked pumpkin mixture; put in baked pie crust.
Let
set
until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream, nuts and maraschino cherries.
Double recipe makes 3 pies.

title: tomato soup
directions: If too thick, add V-8 juice. Simmer 1 hour. Makes a crock-pot full.

title: chicken cord de bleu
directions: Pound chicken or turkey breast until flat.
Lay a slice of ham and a slice of cheese over the breast.
Roll together and hold with a toothpick.
Place in a baking dish.
Next, dilute cream of chicken soup with milk (3/4 of the can) and pour over the chicken or turkey breast.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: basic muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients.
Pour liquid into dry mixture and stir until just blended.
Place in muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
For sweeter muffins, use 1/3 cup sugar.

title: black cherry salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve black cherry gelatin and unflavored gelatin with the boiling water.
Add cherry liquid, Port wine, cherries and pecans.
Pour mixture into a lightly oiled or sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate salad until it is firm. Cut in squares with a hot knife.
Serve salad on lettuce leaves and top with mayonnaise.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate mallow nut sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine water and chocolate syrup. Pour into 2 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle marshmallows and walnuts over top.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in small bowl with your fingers.
Add buttermilk and stir. Add melted butter and stir. Pat dough out on a floured board into 3/4 inch rolls. Place in pan. Dough should be very soft. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar, pineapple juice, lemon juice and cold water.
Mix well and freeze for 2 to 7 days. Remove punch from freezer approximately 8 hours before time to serve.
When ready to serve, mix partially frozen mixture with ginger ale.

title: shrimp with pasta(microwave)
directions: Prepare marinade by combining olive oil, wine, garlic, scallion, black pepper and shrimp.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Prepare macaroni.
Microwave margarine for 1 minute.
Add shrimp marinade.
Cover and microwave on High 7 minutes or less, depending on fresh or frozen shrimp.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Pour over macaroni.
Serve with parsley and Parmesan.
Serves 2.
Prep time:
1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: nut cake(easy, easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; mix all ingredients together except nuts.
After mixing well, add 1/2 pound walnuts, chopped.
Grease baking dish (round loaf) and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mini barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into meat balls, about the size of walnuts. Brown on all sides, then add to Easy Barbecue Sauce in saucepan. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: onion cheese sticks
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk to soft dough.
Mix in cheese and knead lightly.
Pinch off balls.
Roll into sticks.
Roll in soup mix to coat and cook on paper towel 6 to 8 minutes or until firm.

title: macaroni salad with tuna and green beans
directions: Soak tuna in lemon juice in small container overnight. Mix green beans and dressing in small container overnight. Mix other ingredients together. Add tuna and green beans; mix well. Chill until serving time.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Garnishes with additional hard-cooked eggs and green pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender in salted water.
Mash and add all other ingredients except 4 crackers and small amount of butter.
Put 4 crackers, broken into crumbs and buttered, on top. Add paprika, Parmesan cheese and fresh parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Wash 2 average size ray sweet potatoes and grate; do not peel. Mix all ingredients and place in iron skillet in a 400° oven, stirring occasionally, until well done.
Remove from skillet and form into a loaf.
Let cool and slice for serving.

title: peanut brittle cookies
directions: Sift the flour, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Cream the butter.
Add brown sugar gradually; cream well.
Blend in vanilla and 2 tablespoons beaten egg (reserve remaining egg).
Add dry ingredients and 1/2 cup peanuts; mix thoroughly.
Spread or pat dough on greased 14 x 10-inch baking sheet.
Brush with remaining egg; sprinkle with remaining peanuts.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 minutes on a 14 x 10-inch baking sheet.
Do not overbake. Cut or break into pieces while warm.
Can be frozen.

title: hershey bar chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in double boiler or in microwave on defrost.
Whip the cream.
When chocolate is cool, mix in the cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: judi's egg rolls
directions: Mix pork and shrimp.
Fry 2 minutes.
Add onions and bean sprouts.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt and sugar.
Make rolls, using Chinese skins.
Deep fry to golden brown.

title: elizabeth's easy sweet pickles
directions: Put whole cucumbers in boiling water.
Let stand until next day.
Pour off water, rinse well and cover with boiling water.
Do this for 4 days.
Then slice cucumbers.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spices.
Then pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Then bring to boil the whole thing and then can into 7 to 8 pints.

title: mock peanut brittle
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and Karo.
Remove from fire.
Stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
May add a few peanuts if wanted.
Mix well and spread on well buttered cookie sheet.

title: marshall field brunch special
directions: For each serving, place 1 or 2 slices of rye bread on plate and then layer each ingredient on top of each other.
Pour dressing on top and serve.
Very filling!

title: carmen's italian chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter and lemon juice.
Combine spaghetti sauce mix and bread crumbs.
Dip the chicken in this mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake 15 minutes until brown. Do not cover.

title: calico salad
directions: Cook frozen veggies about 10 minutes and drain well.
Drain and rinse kidney beans.

title: alice's grandma kazanowski's bread
directions: Combine yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 cup warm milk; let dissolve.
Add remainder of ingredients, little at a time, until well mixed.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled.
Place dough in 2 loaf pans; let rise until doubled in bulk again.
Bake about 40 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in berries. Grease muffin tins and surface of pan.
Pile mixture high in cups. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: bread and cheese kabobs
directions: Cut each bread slice into 6 cubes.
Combine melted butter, Italian seasoning and garlic in small bowl.
Lightly coat each bread cube with seasoned butter; set aside. Dip each cheese cube in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs to coat.
Thread bread and cheese alternately onto 6 long or 12 short skewers.
Arrange skewers on preheated Crock Grill.
Grill 3 - 5 minutes, turning frequently until cheese is hot and bread is toasted.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix together.
Pour over chicken and bake.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Cook 1/3 cup chopped onion in a little hot fat until golden. Add bread cubes and seasonings; toss in skillet until bread is lightly toasted.
Spread stuffing over steaks and roll as for jelly roll; fasten rolls with toothpicks and lace with string.
Roll in flour and brown on all sides in a little hot fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, 1/4 cup onion and catsup.
Cover; simmer 1 3/4 to 2 hours or until tender.
Add green pepper, mushrooms and liquid last 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding for microwave
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients 5 to 6 minutes, until rice is tender.
Standing time:
5 minutes, covered.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add to cooked rice.
Microwave 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour into dessert dishes and chill.
Add some Cool Whip to garnish.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in
a double boiler and cook over boiling
water for about an hour, stirring occasionally. This sauce
will
be thick and will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: king crab sandwiches
directions: Drain crab meat well.
Slice with sharp knife.
Mix with cheese, mayonnaise, celery, olives, onion, garlic salt and lemon rind.
Butter muffins and top with crab mixture.
Place under preheated broiler until cheese is melted and crab meat is hot and bubbly.

title: cherry-pineapple dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Make 1/4-inch slices of butter and arrange them over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add nuts; boil until all liquid disappears, stirring constantly.
Takes about 15 minutes of boiling.
Put on wax paper or buttered dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook elbow spaghetti.
Drain.
Cook chicken, saving broth. Combine all ingredients.
Skim fat off broth.
Add 1 cup clear broth.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add additional broth to casserole, if necessary.
Serves 12.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze juice from lemons for juice (enough to make 1 cup of juice).
Pour into bottle with tight fitting cap.
Add sugar to lemon juice.
Shake the bottle until sugar dissolves.
Add water to taste.
Shake again.
Chill.
Float a slice of lemon in each glass.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk until mixture boils well.
Boil 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and oats.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool.
Yields 30 to 40.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and chopped nuts.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, chicken and dressing (1/2) in a casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk and pour over layer.
Place remainder of dressing over chicken and cook about 30 minutes.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Put stuff in the pan, like spray stuff.
Mix up stuff for the dough then put in the chocolate chips.
Take a spoon and put cookies on the pan you sprayed.
Then you eat the cookies!
That's what Nathan and I love most!
Yum yum!

title: easy stovetop casserole
directions: Slightly precook ham and onions. Add remainder of ingredients and cook on medium heat for about 30 minutes.

title: no bake rice pudding
directions: Cook rice into the 2 1/2-quart water until rice is done. Rinse and drain.
Cook milk, sugar, butter, cornstarch, eggs and vanilla until thickened pour over rice and use a 4-quart pan.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with next 8 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch ball. Brown meatballs in melted shortening.
Pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet.
Stir constantly until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In skillet, melt butter and brown chicken 4 minutes, turning once.
Stir in golden herb with lemon soup mix, blended with water.
Arrange lemon on chicken. Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: deep south coconut pie
directions: Melt butter until lukewarm.
Add flour.
Blend with eggs, sugar, coconut and milk; mix well.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch crust. Bake in moderate oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: hungarian goulash(reduced fat and calories)
directions: Trim all fat from steak; cut into bite size pieces.
Cook in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring often.
Add onion and green pepper; cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in tomatoes, water, paprika, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 45 minutes or until tender, adding more water if necessary.
Serve over hot rice. Serves 4.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften all ingredients and blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and freeze overnight.
When ready to serve, place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O.
Add limeade and stir until Jell-O is dissolved and limeade melted.
Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.
Prepare instant pudding according to package directions.
Spread over firm Jell-O mixture and refrigerate.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip on top.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Measure 3 cups of flour in mixing bowl and add salt.
Measure 1/2 cup water in a 2-cup measuring cup.
Finish filling with shortening.
Dip out shortening, leaving in water.
Mix in shortening and flour, cutting in shortening.
Add vinegar and egg in water.
Beat with fork.
Add to flour mixture.
Makes 4 or 5 pie crusts.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cream to form a very stiff dough. Make out into balls; cool to harden.
Melt chocolate and paraffin. Dip balls; store in airtight containers in refrigerator.

title: bread(extra rich dough for loaves or dinner rolls)
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine Crisco, butter, 2 cups milk and 1 cup water and warm until butter and Crisco are mostly melted.
Remove from fire.

title: insalata di mare(seafood salad)
directions: In large, shallow bowl or deep platter, combine oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, lemon peel and pepper; set aside to mellow.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix by hand the margarine, 1 egg and cake mix.
Pour out into baking dish.
Mix by hand 2 eggs, cream cheese, vanilla and sugar. Pour on batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in a large bowl.
Mix in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of this mixture in a large, flat container and chill until firm. When firm, spread sour cream on top and then gently spoon remaining mixture over sour cream. Chill well.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Press with cookie press or fancy glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle generously on top. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain and mix first 3 ingredients.
Chop the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Mix sugar and vinegar in a bowl and mix well.
Stir everything in mixture.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in others.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tomato pickles
directions: Cut green tomatoes into quarters.
Cut onions into quarters. Chop peppers.
Sprinkle salt over cut up peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Let soak for 4 hours or longer in nonaluminum container. Mix vinegar and sugar and heat to boiling.
Add chopped tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Cook until all are hot.
Place in jars and seal.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chill all ingredients before combining.
Combine juices; add ginger ale last.
Serve immediately after adding the ginger ale. If desired, add a few scoops of frozen sherbet before serving.

title: mozelle peed's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk.
Beat really good so when you add milk the margarine will not "gel" again.
Pour mixture into 2 regular pie shells, not deep dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Bring water to boil with all ingredients except rice and oil. Fry the rice until slightly brown.
Drain from oil.
Add rice to boiling water, cover and cook on low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: lime and applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the heated applesauce.
Add 7-Up.
Put in glass dish until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cheese Sauce:
Mix flour, mustard and 1/2 cup milk until smooth over medium heat.
Add salt, pepper, paprika and slowly add the remaining 2 cups of milk.
Stir until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese and the ham.
Stir to melt cheese.

title: mandarin orange and cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain the oranges thoroughly.
Add to creamed cottage cheese. Add Jell-O and about 6 ounces of Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly and cool before serving.

title: fish stew
directions: Cook onions in oil; stir in tomatoes, seasoning and potatoes. Bring to a boil; simmer 15 minutes.
Add fish and corn; return to boil.
Cook until fish flakes.
Good with cornbread.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in thick slices.
Slice onion.
Parboil potatoes and onion; drain.
Mix soups and cheese.
Layer potatoes, onion and soup mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli, let dry.
Add to other ingredients.
Serve on lettuce or plain.

title: marinated leg of lamb
directions: Marinate leg of lamb for 24 hours in the remainder of the ingredients listed.
Broil or grill on barbecue 15 minutes on one side, 10 minutes on the other.

title: vegetarian chili soup
directions: Saute onion, in oil, in a large pot over medium heat, until tender, but not browned, about 6 minutes.
Add garlic, chili powder and oregano; cook 30 seconds.
Add vegetable broth, stewed tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower and onion in cheese sauce
directions: Break cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Cook for about 10 minutes in salted water.
Remove tops from onions; cook for about 10 minutes in salted water.
Make a cream sauce from the butter, flour and milk.
Add seasonings and grated cheese.
Place in layers in casserole dish.
First the cauliflower, then onions and cream sauce.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350° or until dish is thoroughly heated.

title: herb butter
directions: Core an unpeeled apple and slice into 1/4 inch thick rings. On a large plate arrange the apple rings on which you have spread any of the following:

title: hominy grits casserole
directions: Cook grits and water until thick (about 5 minutes).
Take from fire and add cheese and oleo.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat eggs and add enough milk to make 1 cup, then add to grits mixture.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can substitute Velveeta and garlic powder for garlic cheese.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels into small pieces until you have 2 cups. Mix pretzels with butter and sugar. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Wait for this to cool before mixing filling.

title: mushroom aioli
directions: Combine all ingredients (except oil).
Whisk slowly.
Add oil, at a drizzle until thick.
Serve chilled on leaf lettuce.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in dry gravy mix. Meanwhile, simmer carrots in 1 cup of salted water for 10 minutes. Add the peas; simmer for an additional 3 minutes.
Stir water, peas and carrots into the ground beef mixture.
Place beef and vegetable mixture in a shallow, ovenproof casserole dish (about 9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Top with hot mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese or melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until mixture is hot and topping is lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all together and chill in refrigerator.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry cake mix, melted butter and eggs. Blend well.
Spread on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly
over batter.

title: garden stuffed yellow squash
directions: Wash squash and then simmer in water 8 minutes, or until just tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Cut a thin slice from top of each squash; remove seeds.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat the eggs in a blender.
Add margarine, sugar and flour. Blend thoroughly.
With blender going, add buttermilk and vanilla. Blend thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Test for doneness by inserting knife into center of pie.
If the knife comes out clean, it is done.
If not, bake a few minutes longer and repeat test.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese and seasoning together.
Beat in egg.
Thaw and thoroughly drain spinach.
Add to cottage cheese mixture; mix well.
Set aside.
In bottom of 10 x 14-inch glass baking dish spread thin layer spaghetti sauce.
Layer with 1/3 of dry noodles, 1/3 cottage cheese mixture, 1/3 grated cheese.
Pour 1/3 of remaining spaghetti sauce over all.
Repeat layers 2 more times, ending with grated cheese.
Set aside 60 to 75 minutes before baking.
When ready to bake, pour water around edges.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand in warm place 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry crepe
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Slowly add flour and sugar alternately with milk and water.
Then beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in melted butter.
Chill batter at least 1 hour.

title: banana bread with cherries
directions: Blend sugar with butter or margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add sour cream, vanilla, mashed bananas, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in a few maraschino cherries and ground nuts.
Use big loaf pan or 3 little pans.
Bake in buttered loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick millet loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients, except millet and olives.
Add millet and olives and mix altogether.
Pour into 2 quart "Pammed" casserole dish.
Garnish top with parsley flakes.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: whipped cream chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss the chicken with the celery, parsley, salt and pepper. Add the mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well. Gently fold in the whipped cream until it is well incorporated. Refrigerate the salad for about an hour. Before serving, sprinkle with almonds.

title: swiss broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli spears.
Combine soup and milk. Arrange broccoli in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Top with 1/2 can onions and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown bacon.
Cook onion in bacon fat.
Add other ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add to beans in casserole.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix crumbs, wheat germ, sugar and melted margarine.
Press mixture firmly and evenly against bottom and sides of 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Set aside.

title: cucumber lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water, stirring well.
When cool, add vinegar, onion, cucumbers and salt.
Turn into a mold and chill until firm.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Preheat oven according to brownie package directions.
Bake brownies according to directions; let cool.
Meanwhile prepare mousse according to directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces in food processor or by gently tapping with a hammer. Break up half the brownies into small pieces and place in the bottom of a glass bowl or trifle dish.
Cover with half the mousse, then half the candy, then half the whipped topping. Repeat layers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Combine dry pudding mixes in a bowl; prepare according to package directions, using 5 cups of milk instead of 4 cups.
Let it set about 5 minutes.
In a large serving bowl, place a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of fruit and a layer of pudding.
I use bananas on first layer, followed by pineapple tidbits and strawberries.
Spread whipped topping over all.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cheese; pour over drained pineapple which have been placed in Pyrex dish.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top of this mixture.
Melt margarine.
Pour over top of crackers.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of pineapple juice over flour mixture if you want.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: country cube steak and gravy
directions: Cook steak in a little shortening until brown.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce over steak while cooking.
Remove from pan. Add 2 tablespoons shortening and flour . Stir until brown on medium heat.
Add brown gravy mix.
Stir in water, then milk.
I use a whisk to prevent lumps.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into bowl over steak and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Put dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, soda and salt) in a bowl and mix well.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla, sugar, grated zucchini, crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Mix well by hand. Grease and flour 3 small tins.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Freezes well.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage coarsely.
Cook in boiling salted water for 8 minutes.
Melt butter or oleo in saucepan.
Add flour and blend well.
Gradually add milk, then stir in cheese.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Alternate cabbage and sauce in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with butter crumbs and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread half of cherry pie filling in pie shell; set aside the rest of filling.
Bake shell 15 minutes. Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°.
In a bowl, beat softened cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over hot pie filling and bake 25 minutes (filling will be slightly soft in center).
Cool completely before spooning remaining sour cream around edge of pie.
Fill center with remaining pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: best apple pie
directions: Stir together sugar, cornstarch, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add salt.
Mix with apples and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly and add to apples.
