Pour in pie crust and dot with butter.
Make about 4 slashes on top of crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: davenport brunch
directions: In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish, slice half the cheese to cover the bottom.
Mix seasonings with sour cream; spread half of sour cream mixture over cheese.
Spread crumbled sausage over sour cream mixture.
Break whole eggs on top of sausage.
Puncture each yolk so it will flatten slightly.
Spread remaining sour cream mixture and top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes (until eggs are firm).
Great with fresh fruit and homemade biscuits.

title: mexican deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Transfer yolks to medium bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly, then mound mixture into whites.
Refrigerate.

title: roast chicken and dressing
directions: Crush bread into fine powder. Chop onion and cook in skillet with 1 tablespoons shortening. Mix bread, onion and remaining ingredients in large bowl, adding water as needed. Clean and trim chicken. Wash thoroughly and salt it. In roaster, add 3 to 4 tablespoons shortening and 1/2 cup water. Put chicken in roaster and pack the stuffing in tightly, wherever room. Bake in oven at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil. Cook 4 or 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Start timing when mixture begins to bubble around edges.
When it reaches soft ball stage, remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla, raisins or nuts. Stir vigorously 1 minute or until marshmallows melt and blend.
Working quickly, drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: one-pot pork chop supper
directions: In skillet; brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Separate
cauliflower
into
flowerets. Boil until tender,
12 to 15 minutes. Drain. Place cauliflower in ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole. Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly. Press evenly on cauliflower. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix 1 cup of the pineapple and mandarin orange juice with the pudding mix.
Cook until thick.
Cool and pour over the fruit. Refrigerate.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil water, sugar and corn syrup to hard ball stage.
Add margarine, marshmallows, cream and food coloring.
Pour over 8 quarts of popcorn.
Make into balls
and cool on wax paper. Yields 18 to 24.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour together until thick.
Let cool.
While pineapple mixture cools, slice bananas in the bottom of the pie shell.
Sprinkle with nuts, coconut and then add pineapple mixture when completely cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: boiled venison
directions: For a seven
pound
roast,
parboil
it
in 1 gallon of water to which
has
been
added red pepper, salt and vinegar. Let simmer for 1 hour, then pour off the liquid.
Put meat set in cold water about 30 minutes, pour this liquid off.

title: fresh peach sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and nutmeg in a small saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Add peaches and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in almond extract.
Serve warm over pound cake.

title: marinated chicken
directions: In non-metallic dish, mix first 5 ingredients. Add chicken; toss. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Broil or grill chicken on rack 6 inches from heat for 30 minutes, turning and brushing often with sauce.

title: cabbage cornbread casserole
directions: Set oven at 350°.
In skillet on medium heat, add a teaspoon shortening.
Add cabbage, onion, green peppers, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Saute.
(Do not fry.)
Cover, stirring often, then add cheese soup.
Stir, then remove.
Mix Jiffy cornbread according to directions on the box.
Pour cabbage mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish (any dish can be used, depends on how deep or wide you choose), then pour cornbread mixture on top.
Even out.
Bake until cornbread is done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mash cream cheese and mix with sugar.
Combine Cool Whip and spread over crusts.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover with blueberry pie filling.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: quiche quickie
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Fry onion in bacon fat. Sprinkle bacon, cooked onion and cheese in 10-inch pie pan that has been lightly greased.
Beat remaining 5 ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute by hand.
Pour into pie pan on top of cheese/bacon/onion.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400° until knife in center is almost clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: nikki's favorite sandwich
directions: Mix mayonnaise and tuna fish. Spread on one slice of bread. Cover with the other slice.
Cut into 2 triangles.

title: yum yum salad(reduced calorie)
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in hot water; cool. Prepare Dream Whip per instructions on box (or use low-fat Cool Whip). Add crushed pineapple, Equal, lemon juice and salt to the cooled Knox gelatine. Add grated cheese and prepared Dream Whip to mixture. Refrigerate overnight. Serves 6.

title: dietetic cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine eggs, buttermilk, Sweet 'N Low and oil.
Stir fruit into dry ingredients and stir into liquid.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Mix and add rest of ingredients.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.

title: 3 flavor ice cream
directions: Note:
Two real ripe peaches can be added, if desired.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp and lay in a large baking pan. Heat all ingredients except for pepper and lemon juice in a saucepan until melted and mixed. Pour over shrimp. Sprinkle with pepper. Squeeze lemon juice on top. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with hot French bread.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into microwave-safe dish.
Microwave for 5 minutes or pour into oven safe dish.
Heat at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hula girl tina's hawaiian fried rice
directions: Cook rice first.
Fry or bake bacon on cookie sheet in oven until very crispy, then crumble.
Use bacon grease to saute 2 bunches of chopped green onions, rice, seasonings and bacon on low heat.
Scramble eggs separately and add to other ingredients.
Use last bunch of onions to decorate top when serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add oil and sugar.
Add zucchini, vanilla, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda; mixing well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition. Add chopped walnuts.
Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine water, yeast, sugar and salt with 3 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil and beat 2 more minutes.
Add remaining flour; mix well by hand.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Best to refrigerate overnight.
Pinch off dough; dip in melted margarine.
Let rise about 3 hours.
Bake at 350° to 400°.

title: cool tuna noodle salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first five ingredients until smooth.
Add macaroni.
Toss to coat well.
Add tuna and vegetables.
Toss gently.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Makes 6 to 7 cups.

title: crock-pot western beans
directions: Cook and
drain
ground
chuck.
Combine beef, pork and beans and bacon.	Add green pepper, onion, brown sugar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in a crock-pot on low and let simmer for a few hours.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Drain pineapple and add together with strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill well before serving.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: Heat your Italian waffle iron.
After mix all the ingredients all together.
Drop by teaspoon on the hot iron.
Cool.
Makes a lot.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and put one-half of the batter in a well-greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle one-half of cheese and one-half of green chilies on the batter, then add the rest of the batter.
Spread remaining half of cheese on top and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions; keep warm. Drain clams.
Reserve 1/4 cup juice.
In microwave-safe casserole, cook onion, garlic and margarine, covered, on 100% power until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, pepper and milk.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add clams, juice, olives and parsley.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Toss with linguini.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Cook bacon pieces
in large saute pan until some of fat is cooked
out.
Add
chicken	pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and
cook
until
bacon
is
done.	Add
garlic, thyme, basil, zucchini,
wine
and chicken stock.
Turn heat to medium-high and cook
minute or so.
Add half and half and cook until mixture starts to thicken.	Add spinach, fettuccine and cheese and heat mixture until it is bubbling hot.
Toss to mix well and
turn
out on
serving
plate.
Top
with additional Parmesan, if desired.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together well.
Add egg, salt and chocolate morsels; mix and set aside.
In large mixing bowl mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, salt, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat well.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery, margarine and chicken base.
Cook broccoli and rice.
Mix all ingredients; put into casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Then add dry ingredients, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in figs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Butter 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Line with pineapple.
Top with berries.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over, then cake mix.
Dribble melted butter over mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then slice through in squares to allow juice to escape.
Top with pecans. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Place almonds and sugar in skillet on low heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar caramelizes on nuts.
Cool and break apart.
Combine all ingredients and serve with dressing.

title: easy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir cocoa into melted shortening.
Add sugar and stir until well mixed.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Pour mixture in 9-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
This pie forms its own crust.

title: banana fritters
directions: Peel bananas and cut in half.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Mix to smooth batter with milk.
Beat egg white until soft peaks form.
Fold lightly into batter.
Drop banana pieces into batter then deep fry in hot oil until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Toss in sugar.
Serve hot with cream.

title: onion-bell pepper roasted potatoes
directions: Cut each potato crosswise into 1/4-inch slices, cutting to, but not through bottom of potato.
(Cut potato should resemble a fan.)
Gently insert onion slices and bell pepper strips alternately in slits.
Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Loosely wrap each stuffed potato in aluminum foil.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes; let stand 10 minutes. Yields 8 servings (161 calories per stuffed potato).

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger (mix in all but 1 tablespoon of taco seasoning; mix with hamburger).
Let cool.
Mix together cut up lettuce, diced onion, tomato, beans, cheese and crushed chips. Add hamburger.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thickened.
Add all other ingredients.
Freeze in electric freeze or pour into trays and freeze in your refrigerator.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all of the ingredients and drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake for "only" 10 minutes.

title: lo-cal vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the seasonings.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add seasonings:
red pepper, garlic salt, seasoning salt, etc.
Delete or add additional vegetables.
The flavor is better the longer it stands.
Yields 10 servings. Preparation Time is 1 1/2 hours.

title: "pig taters"
directions: Bore holes in potatoes to stuff sausage in.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: pasta in butter-basil sauce with broccoli
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan (low heat).
Add garlic, basil and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Steam broccoli florets separately to desired tenderness and boil linguine separately according to package instructions.
Toss butter sauce, cooked linguine, broccoli flowerets and Parmesan cheese.

title: indian egg souffle
directions: Cook vegetables in fat until softened in skillet.
Remove from heat.
Drop egg yolks in bowl with milk, curry powder and salt. Mix.
Fold in beaten whites.
Heat skillet.
Pour in egg mixture over low flame.
Cook until firm.
Add vegetables to cover 1/2 of eggs.
Fold over as for omelet.
Transfer to heated plate.

title: vegetable and snack dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Let beef bouillon dissolve in water. Mix remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together well and fold in 1 large carton Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients until smooth.
Mix peanut butter and milk; add to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
combine dry cake mix, pie filling, flour, nuts,
oil, extract and eggs.
Beat at low speed until completely moistened,
about 1 minute.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium	speed. Put batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge pie
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch with wire whisk.
Beat in milk and egg gradually until smooth.
Microwave on High, stirring 3 times, for 7 to 8 minutes until mixture thickens and boils.
Beat vigorously.
Blend in peanut butter.
In small bowl, combine 1 cup peanut butter mixture and chocolate chips until melted and smooth.
Spread in pie shell; cover in plastic wrap and chill.
Cover surface of peanut butter mixture with plastic and chill for 45 minutes or until cool, but not set.
Whip the cream to soft peaks; fold in peanut butter mixture and spoon over chocolate layer.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: liver with honey and vinegar (microwave recipe)(liver haters will love this one)
directions: Microwave Instructions:
Combine all ingredients except liver in a 1-quart dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes or until green pepper is soft.
Pour boiling water over liver; let stand 3 minutes.
Drain and dry.
Add liver to other ingredients. Cook for 2 minutes or until liver is done.
Serve hot.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown onion in 1 tablespoon of oil, then add ground chuck and let brown.
Drain excess oil and add salt, Ragu sauce and spaghetti sauce mix to ground chuck and onion.
Let simmer and add water as needed. Boil noodles for 6 minutes, adding 1 tablespoon of oil and salt to boiling water.
Spread noodles into buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Spread layer of meat sauce at least 1/2-inch thickness, then spread 1 1/2 cups (approximately) Mozzarella cheese and approximately 1/4 cup of Ricotta cheese.
Repeat so that you have 2 layers.
Add third layer of noodles and top with meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheeses are melted.

title: shirley's pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, and baking powder together.
Cream Crisco and Oleo well.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time. Then add flour mixture with milk.
Then add flavorings.
Beat well.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a deep skillet.
Cook garlic and onions 2 to 3 minutes.
Add celery, zucchini, cabbage, carrots and green pepper. Cook 2 or 3 minutes and add mushrooms, water chestnuts and soy sauce.
Stir and cook for 3 or 4 minutes.
Crunchy and good with any meat.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, onion, pepper and pimento in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of Doritos.
In a saucepan, simmer 1/2 of cheese, mushroom soup, chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes; pour over chicken.
Stir.
Put the remainder of melted cheese on top; sprinkle with remainder of Doritos.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven or until heated through.
Freezes well.

title: williamsburg tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease shallow casserole.
Saute onion in butter until soft, not brown.
Add bread cubes and brown sugar, stirring over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and season to taste.
Pour into prepared casserole and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry cranberry salad
directions: Cut up frozen strawberries and set aside.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Follow package directions for pie crusts.
Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain and rinse in colander.
Place back in pan and add all other ingredients, except 1 cup shredded cheese.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 425°, until crust is brown.
Remove and sprinkle with remaining cheese, then return to oven to melt, about 5 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Batter will be very thin.
Fry in a skillet or on a griddle until light brown.
When well done, fill with applesauce, cottage cheese or apple jelly and roll up.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Put all ingredients in 200° electric skillet or in slow cooker on low.
Let simmer for 2 hours.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until creamy or well mixed.
Add flavorings and continue to beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Put in cold oven.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit; heat and dissolve jello in hot juice. Add cream cheese while hot, then milk, fruit and pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: cream cheese pudding dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; mix well.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, remaining sugar and 2 tablespoons of milk in medium bowl.
With electric mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth. Fold in 1 3/4 cups of the Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Layer with pecans.
Pour remaining milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix. Mix with electric mixer on low speed until well blended or 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over pecan layer in pan.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Chill several hours or may freeze.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Cook, bone and cut up into large pieces the chicken.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch pieces.
Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa. Mix all together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese. Refrigerate 24 hours (very important).
Bake at 300°
for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Heat thoroughly and serve over meat loaf.

title: red river pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan.
In large heavy saucepan or double boiler over low heat, melt chocolate with butter, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Whisk eggs, brown sugar, sugar and liqueur into chocolate mixture until well combined.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until tester comes out barely clean.
Cool in pan on rack; cut into squares.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk; add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad(from atlanta, georgia)
directions: Mix chicken, celery, salt, onion and lemon juice and mayonnaise ahead of time and let stand until flavors mix.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix almonds into mixture.
Put into baking dish; top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips and heat until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: cleo spencer's opossum and sweet potatoes
directions: Clean, dress and wash opossum well.
Place in refrigerator freezer overnight.
Drain and wipe dry.
Season well with a mixture of spices.
Place in baking pan. Cover with thin slices of bacon and bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste often. During the last 1/2 hour of baking, arrange sweet potatoes that have been parboiled around meat.
Bake until brown, basting with drippings. Serve with cornbread and country salad.

title: chicken chablis
directions: Saute chicken in melted butter about 4 minutes on each side. Remove chicken.
Add Chablis and jelly to pan drippings.
Simmer until jelly is melted, stirring constantly.
Return chicken to the sauce.
Add raisins.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Blend wafers in blender.
Cut up candy and nuts.
Stir in milk, candy and nuts.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Form into a roll.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Chill, slice and serve.
Keep in fridge.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat orange juice and water until hot. Add jello and stir until dissolved. Chill until syrupy. Heat until fluffy.
Beat in sherbet and sour cream. Add remaining ingredients; chill until set. Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: In Dutch oven, cook the ground beef, chopped onion and minced garlic until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.

Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano, salt and basil. Bring meat mixture to boiling. Boil gently, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring sauce occasionally. Remove meat mixture from heat. Stir in drained spaghetti.
Place half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Top with remaining meat/spaghetti mix and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: portuguese country bread
directions: In large bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt and flour 1 cup at a time.
Mix with hands.
When no longer sticky turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Knead for 10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Punch down and knead for 5 to 8 minutes.
Form into oval loaf and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise again for about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk.
Put dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and coconut.
Drop from a teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
Makes about 60.

title: poppyseed chicken
directions: Spray an 11 x 13 inch casserole dish with Pam.
Place chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix soups, almonds, and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Mix crackers, poppyseed, and melted butter.
Spread on top of mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 8.
This recipe can easily be doubled for a large crowd and is great for potlucks!

title: joann's hot taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add seasoning mix and water; simmer.
Remove from heat and add tomato sauce and refried beans.
Put in pan and cool.
Layer olives, sour cream and taco cheese on top.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a round plate.
Cover with shrimp sauce.
Sprinkle thawed shrimp over top.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix.
Pour over chicken mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; put in casserole dish.
Add onions, cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise, eggs and butter.
Mix well. Top with grated cheese and seasoned mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: attention shrimp!!
directions: Combine seasoning with paprika.
Add half of spice mixture to butter and stir.
Dip shrimp into butter mixture to coat and place in single layer in large foil-lined pan.
Pour any remaining butter mixture over shrimp.
Broil close to high heat until pink, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining half of spice mixture over shrimp and boil 30 seconds more.
Present shrimp with spiced side up and serve pan drippings as dipping sauce for bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salty water until tender.
Drain.
Combine squash, sour cream, pimentos, cream of chicken soup, carrots and onions.
Mix stuffing and butter.
Line a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with stuffing mixture, reserving a small amount for topping.
Fill dish with squash mixture and remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Drain all cans of beans. Mix all. Saute crackers in butter. Place on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend 2 cups flour, 2 sticks butter and 1 cup nuts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.
Mix together 1 cup confectioners sugar, 1 package cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over layer.
Mix together 2 packages instant lemon pudding and 3 cups of milk.
Spread evenly over second layer.
Top with Cool Whip and walnuts.
Chill.

title: speedy turkey hash
directions: Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Crumble turkey and onion; stir.
Cook until turkey is no longer pink.
Drain.
Stir in potatoes and garlic.
Put in Manwich; cover and cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy breakfast cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan or jelly roll pan for thinner cake.
Before baking top with a mixture of flour, brown sugar, white sugar, oleo and oats.
Blend with pie crust blender.
Sprinkle over cake.
Bake as directed.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch, water and lemon juice until thick. Add Jell-O and peaches.
Put in baked pie shell; chill and cover with Cool Whip.

title: ham logs
directions: Mix
together all ingredients and shape into logs (6 to 8 logs per pound of meat).
Line baking sheet with foil.	Lay logs on pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ann marie's carrot cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add the sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add the carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix
together
the
first
9 ingredients.
Pour mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.	Mix the cake mix and melted oleo; this
will be crumbly-gooey.
Put on top of the pumpkin mixture. Top
with
the
chopped pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for
60 minutes,
or
until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: banana boats
directions: Carefully slit top of each banana lengthwise.
Cut away banana top leaving 1-inch uncut at each end and 1/2-inch on each side (use scissors).
Empty whipped topping into bowl.
Scoop out each banana in small pieces with teaspoon into bowl.
Save banana peel shell.
Fold banana pieces into topping, then fill each shell with 1/4 of the mixture.

title: 24 hours pickles in a crock
directions: Bring water, vinegar, sugar and salt to a boil; let cool. Pour over pickles; add dill, garlic and spices.
Put in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: dr. finco's italian chicken
directions: Thaw chicken breasts.
Place 2 or 3 at a time in gallon Ziploc bag and pound on both sides until very thin.
Mix bread crumbs, flour and seasonings in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix milk and eggs.
Sprinkle each pounded chicken breast with Parmesan cheese. Place slices of Mozzarella cheese on 1/2 of breast, fold chicken in half to cover cheese.
Cover with crumb mixture; dip in egg mixture; dip again in crumb mix.
Cook 15 to 30 minutes in enough oil to cover bottom of electric skillet.
Turn once.
Add more oil, if necessary.
Use medium temperature (250° to 275°) to be sure chicken is completely done and crust does not burn.
Serve with bread sticks, green beans and Fettucine Alfredo.

title: chocolate kisses cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter.
Add both sugars, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light. Sift flour and soda together.
Add to first mixture.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° until cookies begin to brown lightly.
Place a chocolate kiss on top of each cookie.
Return to oven for just a moment.

title: old time corn relish
directions: Boil corn 10 minutes in unsalted water; drain.
Put in ice water.
When easy to handle, drain.
Use a sharp knife to cut from cob.
Do not scrape.
Avoid corn milk.
Measure and reserve 2 quarts corn.
Keep 8 pints and lids immersed in separate kettles of simmering water until ready to use.
In steel kettle, mix celery, peppers, onion, vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed. Boil for 5 minutes.
Blend flour with mustard and turmeric.
Then mix with cold water and form a paste, stirring rapidly to form a paste.
Ladle a little of the hot pickling liquid into flour paste, stirring rapidly to blend.
Mix paste into kettle and boil, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add the corn; cover and boil 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Pack hot relish into hot jars to 1/4-inch from top.
Run thin blade knife around inside edge of jars to release air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims and seal jars.
Process for 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Remove jars and cool completely.
Let stand for about 3 weeks before serving.

title: onion dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Serve with chips or use as vegetable dip.

title: banana pudding(old fashioned)
directions: In the top of double boiler, combine sugar, flour and salt; stir in milk. Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened. Beat egg yolks and add to hot mixture gradually. Continue cooking for another 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add vanilla. Line a casserole dish with vanilla wafers, then sliced bananas. Pour a portion of custard over bananas; repeat layers, pouring rest of custard on the top. Beat egg whites until fluffy, adding 1/4 cup sugar. When egg whites form stiff peaks, pile on top of pudding. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 5 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm or chilled.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring the honey and sugar to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the jello.
Pour mixture over the popped corn.
Butter your hands; make into balls.

title: boston brown bread(1 loaf)
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a buttered loaf pan.
If you prefer a round loaf, use round tin cans.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, syrup, margarine and salt.
Stir constantly, bringing to boil over medium heat.
Without stirring boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Place popped popcorn into large roaster and cover with syrup mixture.
Coat well.
Bake 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool, stirring frequently. Place in tightly covered container.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, oregano, tomatoes and 1/2 to 1 cup water.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes; stir often.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.
Layer 1/2 the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with 1/2 the Ricotta filling; add 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of the meat sauce.
Repeat. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Saute onion and garlic. Add all other ingredients. Simmer soup for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 teaspoon oil.
Add chicken and brown.
Add soup, water and vegetable combination. Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves four.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: anise cookies
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Roll into balls (small).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mama cleo's apple butter
directions: Dissolve sugar and cinnamon red hots in applesauce over low to medium heat.
Turn heat up.
Boil for 10 minutes after mixture comes to full rolling boil (boil which cannot be stirred down), stirring constantly.
Put immediately into warm jars.
Put on can lids and bands.
Jars will seal as they cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together (except pie crust); pour into crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Lower oven to 350°; bake for 35 minutes.
May be served warm or cooled with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: apple orchard pork chops
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown pork chops over medium-high heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine apple cider and mustard; pour over pork chops.
Cover; cook over medium-low heat for 45 minutes.
Add apples, raisins and green onions; cover. Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Place pork chops and apples on serving platter; keep warm.
Gradually stir combined cornstarch and water into juice.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Pour sauce over pork chops and apples.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and cheese.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Add to broccoli mixture; mix well. Add bacon just before serving.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown beef and sausage along with onion and pepper.
After done, add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: stove-top spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in 12-inch skillet.
Remove bacon from skillet and drain most of the fat.
Cook onion and green pepper in grease drippings over medium heat until onions are translucent. Add bacon pieces and remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 15 minutes or until flavors are blended and mixture is hot.

title: quick microwave casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, blend soup, water, wine and soy sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook in microwave on High power for 9 1/2
to 10 1/2 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Top if desired with crushed crackers or bread crumbs (seasoned works well).

title: easy yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate, covered, for 2 hours. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Let set in tins about 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Combine in large skillet the hamburger, pepper and onion; brown well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into a greased casserole or iron skillet.
Top with your own corn bread batter or the following recipe.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix oil, sugar, 10x sugar and margarine.
Add egg.
Mix in baking soda, cream of tartar, flour and salt.
Mix well and spread in 14-inch greased pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, onion, water and chicken bouillon cubes about 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and mixed vegetables.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese.
Lower heat and cook until ready to serve.

title: simple mushroom rice
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Dissolve beef bouillon cubes in hot water. Combine all ingredients and put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo in oblong pan and add all ingredients in order given.
Pour condensed milk over this and bake in 350° oven for about 25
minutes
or until golden brown, let cool, then cut in squares.

title: potato salad (2 to 4)
directions: Boil 8
to 10 medium potatoes.
When cool, peel, slice or dice into a bowl.
Add salt, 2 teaspoons mustard, 1/2 of medium salad dressing jar, 1 teaspoon sugar and chopped or a pinch of dried onion (to taste).
Mix altogether.
Refrigerate.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into 8-cup mold or dish.
Chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vinegar.
Mix well; then add vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in an unbaked pie shell.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with a wire whisk to remove large lumps. Add oil and next 3 ingredients, stirring with whisk until smooth. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Mix. Put in casserole dish and sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Bake the pie shell.
Mix brown sugar, gelatin, salt and spices in a small saucepan.
Mix the pumpkin, egg yolks and milk and stir into the brown
sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Place in pan on bowl of ice or in refrigerator. Stir occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in granulated sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff and glossy. Fold pumpkin mixture into egg whites. Spoon into baked shell. Refrigerate until set (at least 3 hours).
Top with whipped cream and Caramelized Almonds just before serving.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vinegar, salt, sugar, oil, pepper and water in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cool. Combine vegetables; stir in cooled vinegar mixture.
Cover; place in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: amish chicken and corn soup
directions: In chicken stock, place 1 whole chicken and bay leaf.
Simmer 2 hours until chicken starts to fall off bone.
Saute separately until tender-crisp the carrots, celery, onion and garlic in small amount of oil.
After the appropriate time, remove chicken and remove meat from carcass.
Add vegetables to stock.
Add tomatoes, corn, herbs, salt, pepper and potato.
Return meat to stock. Thicken slightly with cornstarch and water.
Makes 1+ gallons.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in boiling water. Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat eggs well; add salt.
Beat in sugar.
Fold into gelatin.
Fold in cream.
Add whiskey or vanilla.
Chill again until thickened. Turn into baked shell and chill until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped cream if desired.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. Add shortening, eggs and mashed potatoes. Add milk and flour alternately.
Knead. Place in a greased bowl and let rise.
Knead down.
Put in refrigerator or make into rolls as desired.
May leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Saute onion (sliced) in butter until tender.
Set aside. Combine egg, milk, corn, hot sauce and corn muffin mix.
Stir until just moistened.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine onion mixture, sour cream, salt, dill weed and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spread evenly over cornbread batter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with another 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to the directions on the package.
Mix the other ingredients in a bowl and add to broccoli in a casserole dish. Top with bread slices and cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger
directions: You will need wax paper or aluminum.

title: cheese-topped pie(good source of protein)
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, green pepper and onion until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in pimento.
Spread beef mixture in ungreased pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Beat 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup milk, the egg yolks, egg, 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper with hand beater until smooth.
Pour over beef mixture in pie plate.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt 8 minutes on High heat, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; stir.
Cook 1 more minute.
Add soda; stir until light and fluffy.
Pour quickly on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin.
Cool 1 1/2 hours. Break into pieces.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream brown sugar, egg yolk and margarine.
Add flour.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let them soften, then spread them evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: billy bread
directions: All you have to do is put the flour in a mixing bowl.
(It has to be self-rising flour.)
Add the sugar and pour in the can of beer.
The beer's the fun part, because it only takes one can and you probably bought at least a six pack to make the bread.
That leaves five cans to build up an appetite.
It's also fun to mix up the dough as it foams and fizzes from the beer, and the aroma is heavenly.
As soon as the dough is formed, put it into a greased bread pan and bake it at 375° for an hour or until done.
When it's done, turn it out and brush the loaf with melted butter.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend the 3 ingredients together until smooth.
You may add nuts to mixture (optional).
Serve with apple slices.

title: butternut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 18 muffin cups or two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans; set aside.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, lemon peel, salt, cloves and nutmeg.
Add eggs, oil, juice and vanilla.
Stir until just combined.
Add squash.
Spoon into muffin cups or loaf pan.
Bake muffins 30 to 35 minutes or loaf 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 1 baked pie shell.

title: pineapple cheddar crunch
directions: Drain pineapple and pour in bottom of 13 x 9 casserole dish. Stir together sugar, flour, and cheese.
Sprinkle over pineapple. Mix crackers and margarine and pour over cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: house salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all but nuts together thoroughly.
Shape into ball.
Chill overnight.
Roll into nuts.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: sausage surprise
directions: Brown sausage and onion; add chopped vegetables and water. Cook on low until veggies are done.
Season to taste.

title: clams casino dip
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes, clams with juice and lemon juice. Simmer in 1/4 pound margarine, onion, garlic, pepper, parsley, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
Mix all ingredients together, including the bacon.
To this mixture, add seasoned bread crumbs. Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix together and press in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix with jello mix.
Add water and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat; add oil and beat well for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan.
Use time on box but don't allow to brown too fast as center takes more time.

title: mock orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and whip until frothy. Pour into chilled glass.
Yields 1 glass.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Spread apples evenly in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place butter in small glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on Low for 45 seconds to 1 minute until softened.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour and add to mixture; add cocoa. Stir in coconut and pecans. Bake in long cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Cook the tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Marinate in some of the dressing.
In a large glass bowl or casserole with straight sides, cover the bottom with thin layer of dressing.
Next layer cabbage, spinach, tortellini, tomatoes, mushrooms and green onions.
Pour dressing over top; sprinkle with bacon.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.
This may be increased to any amount with just using a larger serving dish.

title: brenda's potatoes
directions: Peel, boil and shred potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking dish in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden and slightly crisp on edges.
Prepare the day before, if desired.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make batter of flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour into margarine.
Stir.
Add fruit pie filling.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipping cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Then fold in zucchini and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.
Okay to freeze.
It's very moist!

title: oyster bisque(thanksgiving dinner - mallory farms)
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan.
Saute celery and shallots until tender.
Blend in flour.
Stir, cook 5 minutes more over low heat. Add all other ingredients EXCEPT Half & Half and Tabasco.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add warm Half & Half and Tabasco.
Pour into mugs. Top with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: fran (logan) plant's corn dogs
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk and stir into cornmeal mixture.
Dip hot dog (pierced with wooden skewer or popsicle stick) into cornmeal mixture.
Deep fry at 375° until golden brown.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade concentrate with Eagle Brand milk; stir in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave:
Microwave process cheese spread and salsa or tomatoes and green chilies in a 1 1/2-quart bowl on High for 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring after 3 minutes.
Mix in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until nearly done.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until done.
When done, sprinkle with shredded Monterey cheese and serve.

title: soup-burgers
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a skillet with onion, then drain liquid off.
Add soup and seasoning.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes on low heat, stirring to blend all flavors.
Can serve on toasted buns or white bread.
(Do not add water to soup.)

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator for 4 days.
Each day mix well with hands.
On 5th day, shape into 5 logs and put in broiler pan.
Bake for 8 hours at 150°.
Cool, package and freeze.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt. Shape into 50 small meat balls (1/2-inch).
Place in shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Broil until brown; turn once.
In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour over meat balls. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: roasted garlic soup
directions: Roast garlic on a baking sheet in oven at 350° for 1 hour or for 10 minutes in microwave at full power.
Let cool.
Separate the cloves and peel.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Add ingredients together.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch pan to congeal.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: strawberry pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine noodles, turkey, peas and carrots in large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Pour cheese sauce over other ingredients and mix.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (buttered).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Mix ingredients and add to first mixture.
Heat thoroughly, stirring slowly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry salad
directions: In a large bowl mix all the Cool Whip and the milk; mix well. Stir in the pie filling and the pineapple; mix well.
Stir in nuts. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix altogether with electric mixer.
Heat oven to 325°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: southwestern potato salad
directions: Bake or boil potatoes until tender.
Drain (if boiled) and cool.
Coarsely chop potatoes.
Combine other ingredients and mix lightly with potatoes.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot overnight egg bake
directions: Beat eggs and milk together. Add rest of ingredients. Put into ungreased crock-pot. Cook on low 8 hours.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add frozen berries and juice, pineapple, bananas, Cool Whip and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex and freeze.
Can be stored many days in the freezer and does not require a cover.

title: 2 egg cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Continue to cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until well blended. Add flour
mixture and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour,
beating after each addition.
Bake at 350° until done. Makes 2 layers.

title: beefy barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thick.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks with Pet milk diluted with 3/4 cup water.
Cook until thick; add vanilla.
Put into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips. Dredge in flour, salt and pepper. Brown in fat. Add mushrooms, onion and garlic. Stir in broth. Cook, covered, for 1 hour. Add sour cream and heat. (Do not boil.) Serve over 3 cups cooked rice.

title: easy chicken melt
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Line baking dish with chicken halves.
Top with slices of Provoli cheese.
Mix can of cream of chicken soup with cooking sherry and pour over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing over top and drizzle melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: red lobster lobster bisque
directions: Prepare lobster by cutting in half lengthwise through the head and the body first.
Remove tail halves, and claw and knuckle sections.
These are the sections with the meat for the bisque. Cut the body into 2-inch pieces.
Heat oil over medium high heat in a 4-quart stock pan and add the chopped onions, garlic, shallots, carrots, celery and all of the lobster.
Cook on medium heat, stirring continually for 10-12 minutes or until the lobster shells start to turn red.
Remove just the lobster pieces which contain meat and let cool for 10 minutes.
Deglaze the pan with the sherry.
Add the peppercorns, cayenne, parsley, bay leaves, thyme and tomato puree.
Cook stirring for another 5 minutes. Place the water and heavy cream into pot and bring to a boil. Remove lobster meat from cooled lobster and reserve for the final presentation.
Add the remaining shells to the creamy stock.
Let simmer and reduce by 25%.
In a separate 3-4 quart pot, melt the butter in medium heat.
Stir in flour with a wire whisk to make a roux.
Lower heat and slowly cook the color and butter for about 5 minutes.
The roux should be blond in color and have a buttery aroma.
When the creamy stock is reduced, strain the pot with the roux, and whip with a wire whisk.
Discard the shell
and vegetable mixture.
Chop the lobster meat into 1/2-inch pieces and stir into bisque.
Salt and pepper to taste. Portion into cups or bowls and garnish with chopped chives.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve drink mix and sugar in 6 quarts water in large punch bowl.
Stir in orange juice concentrate, pineapple juice and strawberries.
Add crushed ice and ginger ale just before serving.

title: low calorie breakfast puffs
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine beans and the water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Cook, covered, on High for 8 to 10 minutes (10 to 12 minutes in low-wattage ovens) or until beans and potatoes are tender, stirring once.
Drain in a colander; set aside.
In the same casserole, stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing, yogurt, milk, onion salt and dill weed.
Stir in beans and potatoes. Cover and chill for 4 hours or until thoroughly chilled.
Stir in chopped tomato.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cover so juice cooks away.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease bottom of bread pan only.
Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, zucchini and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Loosen sides; remove from pan.
Let cool, slice and store in fridge. Makes 3 loaves.

title: blondies
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter over low heat; remove from heat.
Add sugar and stir until smooth and dissolved.
Transfer mixture to larger mixer bowl and beat 1 minute.
Add egg and vanilla.
Continue beating until light and fluffy, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Stir in flour and salt, just until blended. Fold in chocolate pieces.
Spread in an 8-inch greased and floured square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake. Cool completely on wire rack, then cut in squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.

Place in a large pan with undiluted apple juice. Boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of water and stir into apple mixture. Boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 5 minutes. Add cinnamon. Fill pastry and dot with 3 tablespoons of butter. Put on top crust and prick top of crust.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and mix until well moistened.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until done.
Make either 2 loaf pans or one Bundt pan.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir in nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill.
Drop from spoon on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine yeast and 2 cups flour.
Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm.
Add to dry ingredients in mixing bowl; add egg.
Beat at low speed with mixer. Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, gradually stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Roll into rectangle.
Spread butter, cinnamon and sugar. Roll into jellyroll; seal edge.
Cut roll in 1-inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: banana cake
directions: Put in first 6 ingredients.
Add bananas and 1/2 of the buttermilk.
Mix until all the flour is dampened, then beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add remaining buttermilk and eggs. Beat 2 minutes longer.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350°.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Can add any other vegetables as desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is no longer pink.
Place half of the cabbage in a large casserole.
Cover with meat mixture and potatoes.
Add remaining cabbage.
Pour soup over top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° or until cabbage is tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix melted shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop small amount of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter delights
directions: Spread about 1 teaspoon peanut butter on half of crackers. Top with remaining crackers.
Melt chocolate flavored candy coating in top of double boiler or you can melt a few squares at a time in microwave for about 2 minutes.
Dip sandwich crackers in coating, allowing excess to drain.

Place on wax paper to cool. Melt vanilla flavored candy coating just as you did the chocolate. Place mixture in a heavy duty zip-top plastic bag and seal. Using scissors, snip a tiny hole in end of bag.
Drizzle mixture on top of chocolate covered crackers.

title: orange balls
directions: Thaw the orange juice, but do not dilute.
Mix with sugar. Cook until soft ball stage.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix slightly and set aside to cool.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground meat, eggs, onion, bread crumbs, milk, horseradish, salt, mustard and 1/4 cup catsup.
Shape into loaf, pressing firmly.
Spread remaining catsup over top of loaf. Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: brandy apple crisp
directions: Peel and coarsely chop apples.
Combine the first 6 ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Toss well; set aside.

title: date sticks
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in bowl.
Add nuts and dates. Add eggs.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 8 x 10 x 2-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut in narrow strips and roll in powdered sugar.

title: peach delight
directions: Pour peaches and juice into a large glass Pyrex dish. Sprinkle whole box of dry cake mix on top of peaches.
Slice margarine into squares and dot on top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add shortening, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add oats and nuts.
Make into small balls.
Dip tops in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Heat olive oil.
Add garlic and cook until tender. Add wine and some of the clam juice and simmer for 10 minutes. Add clams and heat only until hot. Serve over spaghetti and season with black pepper.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Add gradually vanilla, chopped walnuts and chopped apples.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix ingredients, except vanilla, and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve over ice cream.

title: low country shrimp
directions: Note:
Amounts depend on number of people.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice as directed on package.
Saute onion and celery in oil.
Mix soup, cheese and milk over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Combine broccoli and rice with cheese sauce.
Bake in a buttered casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions and celery; brown lightly.
Drain chicken stock from canned chicken; measure 2/3 cup stock and add to browned vegetables.
Stir in soup, soy sauce, Tabasco and pepper.
Bring to boiling point.
Remove chicken from bones; dice in medium sized pieces.
Add to soup mixture; simmer a few minutes.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle noodles and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour; add milk, vanilla and salt.
Cook on low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Line a bowl with wafers; alternate wafers and bananas (3 layers).
Put bananas on top.
Pour custard over.

title: hush puppies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls in deep fat until golden brown.
Makes two dozen.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Add sugar to chopped apples.
Mix and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add egg, flour, soda and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: season's best shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and
Miracle
Whip until well blended. Stir in remaining
ingredients.	Chill.	Serve
with vegetable dippers.

title: pizza crisps
directions: Marinate sliced tomatoes in oil, garlic and oregano.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Place 1/4 slices of bread on sheet.
Top with cheese, tomato and any topping desired. Sprinkle with remaining oil.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Mix raw potatoes, cheddar cheese soup, and milk.
Place in casserole dish.
Brown hamburger with oregano.
Place on top of potato mixture.
Cover hamburger with tomato soup.
Top with mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: santa claus cookies
directions: Melt white chocolate in double boiler. Dip one end of each cookie in chocolate. Place on wire rack. For Santa's hat, sprinkle red sugar on top part of chocolate. Press one white chip off center on hat for pom-pom. Let stand until set. Dip other end of cookie in white chocolate for beard, leaving center of cookie uncovered. Place on wire rack. With a dab of melted chocolate on the uncovered part of cookie, attach mini chocolate chips for eyes and red hot candy for nose. Place on wax paper until set. Yields 32 cookies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together and microwave or 15 minutes in oven.

title: tuna spread
directions: Leave cheese out at room temperature to soften, then simply mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the flour and sugar together and cut into butter.
Press 3/4 of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the apple pie filling and sprinkle the remaining flour mixture over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken breast sandwiches
directions: Place 1 chicken breast half, boned side up, between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
Working from center, gently pound chicken with flat side of a meat mallet until meat is about 1/4-inch thick.
Repeat the same with other breasts.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp and drain on paper towels.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of drippings and cook chicken in hot skillet 6 to 8 minutes or until no longer pink and juices run clear, turning once.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar and cream cheese until creamy, about 15 minutes with mixer.
Make crust of cracker crumbs and enough melted butter to make them stick together.
Pour creamy mixture into shell and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.
When cake is cool, pour mixture over cake.
Bake 5 minutes in 450° oven.
Cake is better if chilled overnight.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer gently 10 minutes and strain.
Pack eggs in hot sterile jars.
Pour liquid over eggs to cover. Seal jars.

title: pear and cranberry crumble
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In large bowl, stir together 1/3 cup flour, oats and brown sugar. With pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until crumbly. In another large bowl, toss together pears, cranberries, caramel syrup, remaining 1 tablespoon flour and ginger root. Spoon into 9-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with crumb mixture and bake 40 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch strips, then cook per bag directions.
Dice cucumber, tomato, onion and bell pepper; shred carrots.
Drain spaghetti and let cool.
When cooled, mix all ingredients in large salad bowl; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour (overnight is okay).
Serves 10 or more.

title: apple biscuits(low calorie)
directions: Divide biscuits in 1/2.
Place in muffin tins.
Chop apples in pie filling into small pieces.
Spoon a large tablespoon of pie filling into each biscuit.
Cover with the other 1/2 of biscuit. Bake according to directions on biscuit can.
Serves 20.
Each serving is 20 optional calories.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Mix whipped topping, yogurt and strawberries in small bowl. Serve as a dip with fresh fruit. Makes 2 cups.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Remove crust from bread and soak in milk.
Ring milk from bread.
Mix with meat thoroughly.
Add seasonings and mix.
Make 1-inch meat patties.
Preheat the broiler.
Heat 5 minutes on each side.
Add bacon and bread crumbs and bake for 2 more minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash potatoes.
Beat in sugar, butter, cream, salt and sherry until light and creamy. Spoon into lightly greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into ball.
Chill.
Roll in chopped pecans. Serve with crackers.
Cheese ball will be soft.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter; mix with brown sugar. Add eggs and flour. Mix well. Add chips and nuts. Bake in a 13 x 11-inch greased and floured baking dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in salt, pepper and flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Stir macaroni into cheese sauce.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole (microwave-safe).
Microwave for 5 minutes on High or bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with bread, raw vegetables, chips or use instead of sour cream on baked potatoes or in salads.

title: stir-fried spinach
directions: Wash spinach; discard stems and bruised area of leaves. Drain. Add oil to wok, pouring it around sides.
Preheat oven to
325° for
about 2 minutes.
Add spinach and garlic;
toss lightly
to coat
spinach
leaves with oil, about 30 seconds. Cover;
cook
1 minute.
Remove
cover; stir-fry additional 1 minute.
Leaves should
be dark green and glisten.
Add salt, sugar, pepper and sesame oil.
Stir to blend about 30 seconds. Makes 3 to 4 servings.
My children's favorite in late spring.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, margarine, peanut butter, sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Make dough into small balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not hard.

title: bran muffins
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasoning. In a separate bowl mix egg and milk. Dip chicken in egg mixture, and coat chicken with cheese mixture. Place in a baking dish that has been sprayed with a non stick cooking spray. Pour butter over chicken. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries in blender or food processor.
Process until berries are in small pieces.
Put berries in bowl.
Stir in sugar. With mixer, add the rest of the ingredients.
Let set overnight. Nice for Thanksgiving or Christmas holidays.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour and vanilla well.
Add water and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 300°. Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: junior's shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp in liquid crab boil seasoning; salt and pepper to taste. Put onion and bell pepper in blender to get it real fine. Mix all ingredients together in large bowl; then add mayonnaise and Ranch dressing to taste.

title: beef stew
directions: Preheat 6 quart Dutch oven for 3 minutes over medium heat. Brown beef cubes on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and bouillon.
Cover and when vapors escape from cover, reduce heat to low and simmer 45 minutes.
Increase heat to medium.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Cover and when vapor escapes from cover, reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Mix in blender the hot water and unflavored gelatin.
Add Coffee-mate and 1/2 cup hot water; blend.
Add frozen orange juice and crushed ice; blend.
Pour into bowl and some of your favorite fruits such as bananas, peaches, green grapes, coconut, pineapple and apples.
Marshmallows would be good too, and low calorie.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, eggs and cream cheese.
Spread over cake mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Blend until mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add enough milk to fill pie.
Sprinkle with cinnamon on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven back to 400° for another 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese until soft and mix everything but cheese and crab.
Fold in crab and most of cheese.
Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cornbread salad
directions: In large bowl, crumble cornbread.
Add crumbled bacon, diced tomatoes, chopped onions and chopped bell pepper.
Mix together mayonnaise and dill pickle juice in cup.
Pour over tossed ingredients.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Put into graham cracker pie crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until middle is firm.
Use topping of choice.

title: cheese cake tart
directions: Place vanilla wafers in mini cupcake papers.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Pour on top of wafers.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Chill for 15 to 30 minutes, then top with pie filling.
Return to refrigerator.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook each package of vegetables separately as directed.
Drain and toss together.
Mix mayonnaise with milk and fold into vegetables.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: honey french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with tight fitting cover. Shake vigorously and chill.

title: supper in a pumpkin
directions: Cut top off pumpkin; set top aside.
Scoop inside of pumpkin to remove seeds; leave sides intact.
Season inside with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Crumble sausage into skillet with onions; saute until lightly browned.
Add pepper and rosemary.
Stir in all other ingredients and fill pumpkin.
Cook just top of pumpkin with foil.
Place pumpkin on rack in roasting pan with 1-inch water in pan.
Cover all with foil; seal tight and steam at 300° for 3 hours.
Add pumpkin top to bake last hour only to keep it from shrinking.
Set on pumpkin to serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium baking dish.
Top with bacon. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb finely in a bowl.
Add all ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into a deep dish pastry lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown and bubbly in center.

title: pickled squash
directions: Sprinkle salt over squash and onions; let set for 1 hour. Drain.

title: pizza roll
directions: Roll out thawed bread 1/4-inch thick or thinner.
Spread about 1/4 cup melted butter on bread.
Sprinkle garlic salt or garlic powder, Parmesan cheese and oregano on bread. Add meat
and then Mozzarella cheese. Roll in a long roll and secure with toothpicks. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Cut in slices.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and eggs and beat until smooth.
Add drained pineapple, fold in bread cubes.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned and firm.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Mix chicken, Veg-All and soup together in casserole.
Mix milk and Bisquick (will be very thin) and spread over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° until dough on top is brown.

title: festive punch
directions: Recipe makes 50 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Spread bread slices with margarine. Trim the crusts off, then cut bread into cubes.
Spray 9 x 11-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spread bread in bottom of dish. Add sausage over bread, spreading evenly.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over sausage and bread.
Cover casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and continue cooking for 20 more minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Press 1 package of rolls out on a 9 x 13 pan sprayed with Pam. Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice together and pour over crescent rolls.
Then put cherry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Press out the other crescent rolls and place on top of cherry pie filling.
Then glaze top of rolls with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato-basil soup
directions: In a large stockpot, cook mushrooms and onion in hot oil until onion is tender. Add potatoes and both cans of broth.
Boil, then reduce heat. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: fuzzy navel dream
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine and soak sugar and water 15 minutes.
Mix and
toss pecans with remaining ingredients. Place on greased sheet at 350° for 10 minutes. Delicious for salads.

title: cinnamon crinkles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Cream together sugar, shortening and salt until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in milk; add flour mixture and blend until dough is thoroughly mixed.
Chill 1 hour, then make 1 inch balls.

title: taco compuesto
directions: Cook beef, onion, chili peppers and garlic until beef is browned; drain.
Stir in chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Combine tomato, salad dressing and seasoned salt.
Spoon beef mixture into taco shells; top with tomato mixture, lettuce and cheese.
Pass taco sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients, then add liquid ingredients and nuts; mix well.
Coat 2 loaf pans with vegetable spray.
Pour batter in and bake for 1 hour.
Cool loaves for 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: sand tart cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 3 rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap. Chill overnight.
Slice; place walnut on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and milk together until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pie shell.

title: beet molded salad
directions: Slice beets into strips.
Combine jello and hot water; mix with other ingredients.
Put in mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Serve with fruit. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, adding enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on foil paper, spread with peanut butter.
Roll up and chill for at least 1 hour.
Slice into narrow slices.
Keep refrigerated.

title: nana's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water and oats and let set 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: jeff's bacon mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Wrap each mushroom with a strip of bacon, and secure with a toothpick.
Arrange the mushrooms on a medium baking sheet.
Bake approximately 15 minutes in the preheated oven, until the bacon is evenly brown.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese set out until room temperature.

Mix all ingredients together until well mixed, except nuts and paprika. Make cheese into a ball and chill in refrigerator until firm. Pour chopped nuts and paprika out on a sheet of wax paper and roll cheese ball in it.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cheese with orange juice.
Add sugar, vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Freeze in casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter krispie bars
directions: In a large nonstick pot, melt margarine.
Add marshmallows and stir constantly until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter to marshmallow mixture.
Mix well (by hand). Gradually add cereal, a little at a time, mixing after each addition.
When all cereal is added, spray a rectangular casserole dish with nonstick vegetable spray.
Press Krispie mixture evenly into pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter, stirring in flour, dry mustard and salt.
Blend in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Stir until melted.
Combine macaroni and cheese sauce; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish (approximately 2-quart).
Top with cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until
hot and bubbly.

title: crab rangoon(appetizer)
directions: Blend crab meat with cream cheese and seasoning.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in center of wonton skin.
Moisten edge of skin with beaten egg white.
Fold square into triangle and twist to seal.
Fry in oil heated to 375°.

title: pie crust
directions: Put flour
and salt in bowl.
Put Crisco into mix until crumbly.
Beat egg and put in vinegar and water together with egg and add to flour.
Mix good.
Makes 4 (8-inch) pie shells.

title: soft oatmeal apricot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Beat in molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir into batter.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Shape into 1 in.
balls and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes....
or until browned.
Yield 7 dozen.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in a large pan (large enough to serve as a mixing bowl).
Add brown sugar; mix and cool.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Fold in sifted dry ingredients, then nuts and chips.
Spread in greased 10 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
