title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and bake in 2 small loaf pans at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, crumbled Top Ramen noodles, cole slaw, peas, bell pepper and celery.
Toss well.

title: easy caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place popcorn in large roaster pan. Let stand in oven while preparing glaze.

title: cheese baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Let cool.
Cut in halves.
Scrape pulp from skins and mash.
Add a little milk to make light and fluffy.
Saute onions in butter.
Stir with potato mixture along with salt and pepper.
Pile mixture back in potato shells.
Cover top with grated Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess grease.
Add barbecue sauce, instant onion and garlic powder and mix well.

title: kay's dump cake
directions: Pour crushed pineapple in an oblong pan and pour 1/2 cup pecans over pineapple.
Put dry cake mix into pan on pineapple and pecans.
Pour second 1/2 cup pecans over cake mix.
Slice butter over cake mix and pecans and bake at 325° until done.

title: california nacho dip
directions: Layer in order in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, except sour cream. Reserve small amount of cheeses.
Refrigerate layers for at least 2 hours and then bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes; chop until fine.
Put artichokes in a square pan or casserole dish.
Spread on chilies.
Spoon mayonnaise on top with spatula; spread evenly.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large bowl stir together first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add
remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: yummy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, form all meatballs, cook in greased electric fry pan, mix all soup and milk in large kettle for the oven, put in meatballs and bake at 350 for 2 hours, goes good with mashed potatoes and corn, the liquid from meatballs makes great gravy!!!!!

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Cream the butter and add egg yolk, confectioners sugar, flour and salt; mix thoroughly.
Chill for at least 20 minutes.
Roll out to 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with star cutter or any other shape you desire and arrange on ungreased cookie sheets.
Beat the egg white until stiff, then gradually beat in the granulated sugar.
Put a spoonful of beaten egg white on each cookie and sprinkle with the chopped nuts (optional).
Bake about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: path finders supper
directions: Heat oil in skillet over low heat.
Add hash browns, sausage, green onion and seasonings.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or to desired brownness.
Spoon cheese spread over potatoes and sausage mixture.

title: chicken lollipop
directions: Wash and clean chicken wings thoroughly.
Cut and scrape meat downwards and marinate with seasoned salt, garlic powder and black pepper for 1 to 2 hours.
In a medium bowl, beat 2 eggs until blended.
Dredge chicken wings in flour one by one (mix the meat in the flour like forming a small ball).
Dip in beaten eggs, then dredge with bread crumbs.
Deep fry in a medium-high heat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot or with hot or sweet/sour sauce.

title: lemon sauce cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and water.
Mix well and put into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Remove cake from oven and poke holes in cake with tines of a fork.
In small saucepan, mix and boil for 1 to 2 minutes, sugar, butter and juice.
Pour over cake; return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: 15 layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, vegetable oil and sugar; add eggs. Mix well. Add flour, milk and vanilla. Mix well and put 4 tablespoons batter into each greased 9-inch pan. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°), or until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan. Cut into squares.
Chill.

title: white beans and ham soup
directions: Saute onion, carrots and garlic in margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mash slightly with potato masher.
Cook for 15 minutes over medium heat.

title: ritzy pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Mix sugar and baking powder.
Add to egg whites.
Beat to stiff peaks.
Fold in nuts and cracker crumbs. Pour into a greased and lightly floured pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Top should be light brown.
Top cooled pie with whipped cream.
Garnish with extra cracker crumbs and chopped pecans.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared pie crust. Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: plucking bread
directions: Cut biscuits in half; roll each into balls.
Melt butter; add sugar and cinnamon.
Mix.
Place in ungreased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place on bottom rack and cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon microwave english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, raisins, dry yeast, sugar, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Combine milk and water; heat to very warm. Gradually add to dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 greased loaf pans, Pyrex that have been sprinkled with corn meal.
Sprinkle more corn meal on top.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 45 minutes. Microwave one loaf at a time on High power for 6 minutes and 30 seconds.
Allow to rest 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Slice and toast.
Do not eat until toasted.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken, onion and pepper; cook and stir until chicken is cooked through. Add corn, broth and salsa; bring to a boil.

title: pork hawaiian
directions: Soak chops in soy sauce 5 minutes.
Brown on top of stove, then place in roasting pan.
Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch slices crosswise and put into oven with chops (350°) and cook for 15 minutes.
Add bananas and pineapple.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pineapple juice and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Shell eggs.
Boil vinegar and add seasonings.
Pour vinegar mixture in glass jar and drop in eggs.
Cover, but don't tighten lid until mixture is cool.
Let stand 10 days.
Cocktail onions, beets and beet juice may be used for pink eggs.

title: almond butter cookies
directions: *Do not use self-rising flour in this recipe.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash pickles and pack in jars.
Mix water, vinegar and salt; boil.
Pour over pickles in jars and seal.
A hot pepper may be added, if you like.

title: chicken a la can
directions: Combine soups and water in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, celery and chestnuts.
Stir in well.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch dish (pan).
Add rice by sprinkling on top.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips (1/2 bag).
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and 1/2 cup cream; bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add remaining 1/2 cup cream and cook slowly to very hard ball stage (260°).
Remove from heat; add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into grease 8-inch square pan.
Mark in squares when partially cool.
Cut when cold.
Wrap caramels in squares of waxed paper; keep in airtight container.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: cheesy cauliflower and celery
directions: Cook celery in water and chicken bouillon granules 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Place cauliflower in same pan.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain, reserving the cooking liquid.
In a small saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine; blend in flour.
Add reserved cooking liquid and milk all at once.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in lemon juice. Gradually add cheese; stir until melted.
Combine pecans, oats, wheat germ, sunflower nuts and remaining butter.
Arrange celery and cauliflower in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare cheese sauce and nut mixture.
Pour all the sauce over vegetables.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle nut mixture over.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla, then flour. Add oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda; mix well.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes (may take a little longer).
Makes 9 dozen.

title: chicken cutlets doris
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then mixture, then egg and then mixture again.
Have olive oil heated in skillet.
Brown chicken.
(This only takes several minutes each side.) Drain on paper towels. Serve with pasta and red sauce, garlic bread and salad.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the sugar, syrup and margarine.
Boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in soda.
Pour this on top of popped corn that you've put in a large brown grocery bag. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake real well. Dump onto cookie sheet to cool.

title: yoshie's fried rice
directions: In skillet, fry bacon.
Saute veggies and ham in with bacon grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Don't overcook veggies, leave a little crisp.
Turn off heat and add cooked rice.
Serves 5.

title: working girl's roast
directions: Wrap roast in large piece of foil.
Sprinkle roast with plenty of garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour soup on top of meat, then Worcestershire sauce over soup.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over that. Pour water in bottom of foil.
Pull foil up and seal across top and ends.
Be sure it is sealed tightly, leaving space above and around roast.
Place in pan and put in 250° oven from 7 to 5 p.m.

title: quick fruit dessert
directions: Take flour tortillas and heat in hot grease 2 to 3 seconds to a side; lay flat in pan or on a plate.
After heating all tortillas, spoon some canned pie filling onto each tortilla and roll up like a burrito.
Put all the tortillas in a baking dish and drizzle the powdered sugar and milk mixture over them.
Heat in a 350° oven about 20 to 30 minutes just to heat through.
Or put on individual plates and microwave each one about 1 minute or less.

title: hello dollies
directions: Place in pan in layers.
Pour milk over top of all.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Blend together well the can of milk and the Cool Whip.
Add the rest of the ingredients, mix and freeze.
May add nuts, also.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil butter, brown sugar and syrup 4 to 5 minutes. Add baking soda.
Pour mixture over the popcorn and bake on cookie sheet approximately 50 minutes at 200°.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer in greased casserole:
sour cream, onions, sauerkraut, corned beef, Swiss cheese.
Melt butter and toss with bread cubes. Place buttered bread cubes on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Drizzle Thousand Island dressing over top after serving, if desired.

title: cherries in the forest
directions: Mix box of chocolate cake mix, cherry pie filling, eggs and almond flavoring.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hobo beans
directions: Cook meat, onions and peppers.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and cook until done.
Serve with chips.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Grease an 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Place all ingredients (except cheese) into a dish and mix well.
Sprinkle cheese over top; bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer in pie (vegetables, chicken and soup).
Bake at 425° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: souper meat ball casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Combine the ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Shape into 20 meat balls.
In large skillet, melt butter and slowly brown meat balls. Arrange meat balls in a shallow casserole.
Combine soup, cooked mixed vegetables and 1 cup cheese.
Pour over meat balls. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over casserole.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix juice with sugar, pineapple and cheese.
Combine crackers and margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy strawberry nut bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and sugar.
Add the eggs, vegetable oil, strawberries, and pecans to the dry ingredients.

title: glenda's deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in half.
Remove yolk from white and set white aside.
Mash yolks with a fork and add the mayonnaise, mustard, red pepper, pickles and salt; mix well.
Spoon mixture back into egg whites.
Dash each egg with paprika.

title: coconut custard blender pie
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Put all ingredients in blender or processor; blend on high for 10 seconds.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Serves 8. Makes its own crust.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with foil.
Butter the foil.
Arrange marshmallows in pan.
In a double boiler or microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over marshmallows.
Chill completely.
Cut between marshmallows.
Makes 3 dozen.
These are fast to make and kids love them.

title: low calorie frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Add juice from fruit cocktail and beat well in electric mixer.
Add fruit, cherries and marshmallows, blending through cream cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan and freeze.
Serves 8.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Roll out and cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep fry at 325° until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Grease baking dish and place chicken breasts in dish.
Cover with 1 layer of cheese.
Pour soup, diluted with milk, over cheese. Sprinkle crumbs over chicken and cheese.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water.
Mix salt, sugar, shortening and beaten eggs in rest of water; add yeast and flour and mix well.
Pour into container.
Cover and place in refrigerator; make into rolls as needed.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: apple raisin ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut apples into small pieces.
Combine apples with raisins, cake mix, sugar/cinnamon and lemon juice. On a baking stone, make a circle with crescent triangles, wide sides overlapping.
Press seams together.
(It will look like a sun with a hole in middle.)
Spoon mixture along edge of circle in a ring. Lay each triangle point over mixture and press along inside seam. (Mixture will not be completely covered.)
Whisk egg white with 1 teaspoon of water and brush top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to box directions.
Cook vegetables according to package.
Combine drained pasta and vegetables with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a Bundt pan that has been sprayed with a cooking oil. Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cool slightly. Can either dust with powdered sugar or glaze with any frosting.

title: pizza dippers
directions: Brown sausage; crumble, drain and set aside.
Combine flour, cheese and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the size of small peas.
Add sausage.
Add water, a little at a time, tossing and stirring with fork until dough is moist enough to hold together.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar, oleo and eggs.
In separate bowl, pour 1 cup of the flour over the fruit and coat the fruit with flour. Add fruit, remainder of flour and other ingredients; mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 300°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on jelly roll pan (ungreased).
Pat together and bake at 375° for 13 minutes or until browned.
Mix together softened cream cheese and Hidden Valley dressing and spread over crust.
Place fresh veggies on cream cheese.
Possible veggies:
cauliflower, broccoli, tomato, carrots, all cut tiny or diced.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Cut in shortening with fork.
Combine egg and milk.
Add flour mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in cooker 1 hour, then bake in oven 1 hour or 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Chop rhubarb.
Start cooking without water on low heat.
Add sugar after rhubarb is juicy.
Cook and skim until clear.
Add strawberries and bring to boil.
Do not cook after adding strawberries as they will dissolve.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add oil followed by dry ingredients.
Mix well with an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Fry on hot griddle.

title: frosty cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine whipping cream and sugar.
Chill bowl and beaters thoroughly.
In medium bowl, soften cheese.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Beat cream mixture until stiff.
Fold into cranberry mixture.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Cover.
Freeze until ready to use.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Serves 9.

title: green stuff(jello salad)
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into pan.
Add sugar, salt and jello.
Bring to a boil and let cool.
Add mayonnaise, cottage cheese and pineapple.
Mix well, then add Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: strawberry tea bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine until softened.
Add corn syrup and sugar to margarine; beat until smooth.
Add eggs. With mixer at low speed, beat in strawberries and vanilla.
With wooden spoon, stir flour mixture into strawberry mixture just until moistened.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Bread slices best on second day.

title: hash brown potato cheese bake
directions: Pull apart hash browns into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Put in a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Layer chicken, broccoli, sauce, cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add mushrooms, broth and celery soup. Bring to boil, then remove from heat.
Add sour cream, milk and wine.
Layer with bread slices and swiss cheese.
Pour remaining mixture on top and bake at 325-350 degrees for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pan and cook about 10 minutes; cook until it forms a soft ball, then beat.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the
first	3
ingredients	together and press in a sheet cake pan.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
While it is still hot, punch holes in the top and pour the Eagle Brand and cream of coconut over the top.
Allow to cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs
with milk.
Mix and stir in the flour,
sugar and
nutmeg.
Last,
fold
in
rhubarb
and vanilla. Pour
into unbaked
pie
crust.
Dot
with
butter. Cover with lattice
top (made with pie crust left over from 2 pie
crusts). Bake until lightly brown at 425° for 20 minutes or 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spoon corn bread(my mother's recipe from the deep south.)
directions: Mix corn meal with 1/4 cup cold water.
Add boiling water and stir.
Add salt, sugar and egg. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture. Add melted butter. Pour into casserole dish and bake in hot oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Gently skin eggplant and slice thinly lengthwise.
Dip in egg and then bread crumbs.
Fry in pan with oil until medium gold; drain and set aside.

title: a pound cake(by kathering brown, a friend)
directions: Blend soft butter and sugar.
Add mace and flavoring.
Beat in 4 eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour and remaining egg.
Mix well.
Put in a well-greased tube cake pan.
Place in a cold oven. Set oven at 300°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove from pan.
Keep in tightly sealed cake box or foil.
It can be frozen.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole.
Top with paprika.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ajilimojili sauce
directions: Grind everything and mix.
Add oil and lime juice and stir well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with crushed cornflakes.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.

title: caramel drops
directions: Cook ingredients, except marshmallows and graham crackers, to a ball.
Add marshmallows and graham crackers.
Lay on wax paper.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all
ingredients
well and cover. Refrigerate for 3 days. On the fourth
day, make 3 rolls 2 1/2 inches thick x 8 inches at night.
Bake on broiler rack so it can drain at 150° for
10 hours.
Let
cool
and
wrap.
Can
be frozen or used immediately. Must be refrigerated for use.

title: my best chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, onion, peas and carrots, potato and butter and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Mix the flour, milk, chicken broth and cream of celery soup and pour on top.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar well.
Add onion; beat well.
Add oil gradually, heating all the time.
Dressing is better if made in blender.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chocolate-pecan fritters
directions: In a double boiler, melt the milk with the caramels, stirring occasionally. When melted, use wooden spoon to stir in pecan halves.
Drop by spoon onto buttered wax paper.
Let cool at least 15 minutes.

title: bacon and onion breakfast pie
directions: Spoon onions over pie shell.
Cover with cheese and bacon. Combine other ingredients and pour mixture over cheese.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes clean.

title: festive fajitas
directions: Cut chicken breasts into thin strips.
Saute in oil 4 minutes. Add green peppers and onion and saute 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add cheese and stir until cubes melt.
Fill each tortilla, top with tomatoes and fold.
Serve hot, with sour cream and salsa.

title: green peppermint topping
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend ingredients together.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Sift all together. Two or 3 times beat the egg whites until stiff.
Whip cream until stiff.
Add the egg whites to cream and mix thoroughly.
Then add flavoring.
Alternately add the dry ingredients with the cold water beating hard between each addition.
Butter pans and bake in a fairly hot oven.
This makes 2 layers.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, but pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: orange rice
directions: Melt margarine in skillet to coat bottom.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add rice, celery and onion.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until rice is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: date nut bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 (8 1/2 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Sprinkle soda over dates and add boiling water.
Let cool.
Combine dry ingredients; add sour cream, dates and eggs.
Blend until just moistened.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Place in prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: new york cheesecake (rusty style)
directions: Mix:
Crumbs, 3 Tbsp. sugar and butter.
Press onto bottom of 9 inch spring form pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: cheezy chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken. Add generous cheese slices over entire casserole. Sprinkle generous amount of bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
It makes its own cheezy gravy!

title: custard frosting
directions: In a saucepan, cook milk and flour, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a thick paste.
Take off heat and place in a bowl. Cover with wax paper and cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll in nuts.

title: hominy gem corn muffins
directions: In a large bowl mix all dry ingredients well.
In another bowl mix all wet ingredients well and combine with dry ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20-25 minutes, untill browned.
Makes a moist heavy muffin. Yield:
12 muffins.

title: party rye snacks
directions: Fry sausage and drain grease.
Melt cheese with catsup, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with sausage.
Heat until melted. Spread on bread.
Bake at 350° until bread is toasted on bottom.

title: garden potato pie
directions: Peel and shred potatoes.
Rinse potato shreds well and drain. In large mixing bowl, combine 1 egg, onion, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Transfer mixture to 9-inch pie plate, pat the mixture in the bottom and up the sides of the dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden. Cool slightly on wire rack.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Arrange ham on potato crust.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill until serving.

title: apple orchard squares
directions: Combine flour, salt and 1/3 cup sugar and oleo.
Mix like pie crust.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put apples, lemon juice, cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar in bowl; mix well.
Then put over crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar, egg, milk, nuts and coconut.
Spread over baked apples and bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Combine with the remaining ingredients. Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Chill pie shell.
Mix together sugar, salt and flour.
Add egg yolks which have been slightly beaten.
Add buttermilk, butter and flavoring.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until they peak when beaten.
Then fold into custard mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 325° for 30 minutes or until pie is firm.

title: waffles
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add to dry ingredients, alternating with shortening.
Makes enough batter for 3 to 6 waffles.

title: pineapple refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and egg yolks.
Cook for 1 minute. Take from stove and add jello.
Cool until thick, but not set. Fold in whites of 2 eggs, beaten stiff.
To this add cream, whipped stiff and crushed pineapple that has been well drained.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Combine chicken, noodles, celery, green peppers, onion, salt and mayonnaise.
Set aside.

title: fire house chili
directions: Cook ground chuck and chopped onions until done.
Drain meat and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Soak the poppy seed in the milk for 2 hours.
Cream the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together and add poppy seed mix.
Bake 1 hour in loaf pan at 350°.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Beat 1st three items together.
Fold in balance of ingredients.
Place in crust.
Chill.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Spoon 1/4 cup mix into cup and add hot water.

title: orange jello mix
directions: Mix with 3 cups hot water (a little less) Jell-O, vanilla pudding and tapioca pudding mix.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Add mandarin oranges, drained thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon coconut pie
directions: Beat together until light and fluffy all ingredients except coconut and butter.
Melt butter.
Add coconut and combine with egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust (shell).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach or strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook water, sugar, cornstarch, almond flavoring and food coloring until thickened. Add margarine. Let cool. Stir in fresh peaches or strawberries. Pour into baked pie crust. Top with Cool Whip. Store in refrigerator.

title: microwave vegetable platter
directions: *Cauliflower flowerets, broccoli flowerets, small zucchini and cherry tomatoes.

title: german pound cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar well.
Mix in vanilla, eggs, flour and milk.
Add baking powder.
Beat until batter forms peaks. Bake in greased, floured tube pan at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat. Cover and cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and cool. Fry bacon until crisp, drain on paper towels.
Cook and stir onion in bacon fat until tender.
Stir in sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Boil and heat for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Crumble bacon into hot mixture and potatoes.
Serve hot.

title: liver and onions
directions: Remove heavy blood vessels and outside membrane from liver. Coat slices of liver with flour.
Brown on one side in hot fat. Turn liver.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with onions and add water. Cover pan.
Cook over low heat 20 to 30 minutes or until livers are tender.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Cook rice per package directions.
In casserole dish, put a layer of ground beef, then layer of yellow rice and then a layer of stewed tomatoes.
Repeat same ingredients again.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Put tomatoes in a large bowl.
Add the other ingredients one by one.
Stir gently; spoon the salsa on some Tortilla chips.

title: dr. byrd cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Put all ingredients together and blend. Do not beat.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 20 servings.
Stays moist and fresh.

title: mary ann's liver pate
directions: Cut cream cheese in half.
Mix with sausage and onion.
Line a bowl with Saran Wrap.
Pat mixture into bowl and chill.
Mix milk with remaining cream cheese and blend well. Frost meat mixture with cream cheese mixture.
Garnish with a few whole pecans, if desired.

title: cheesed grits
directions: Cook 1 cup grits as directed on package.
Add cheese, oleo, red pepper and salt.
Mix and let cool.
Beat 2 eggs, add to mixture and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: microwave garlic spread
directions: Boil garlic in 1/2 cup water in 2-cup glass measure for 2 to 3 minutes or until garlic is soft.
Pour off water.
Mix garlic cloves and margarine in blended until very well blended.
Store in refrigerator until needed.
Power Level:
High.
Total Time:
2 to 3 minutes.

title: rhubarb crumble pie
directions: Line pie crust with rhubarb.
Mix eggs in with 1 cup sugar; pour over rhubarb.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Blend in butter; sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: "doggie" biscuits for people and doggies
directions: Mix flours together with salt in large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in
small bowl and stir.
Add yeast and two cups of broth to dry ingredients.
Mix well with hands until dough is stiff.
Add a little more broth if necessary.
Roll out dough on a floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into desired shapes. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Brush with egg and milk mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave overnight.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Spread out in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased), then spread a layer of cut up ham. Then layer Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together eggs, milk and Bisquick; pour over broccoli, ham and cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese peas with water chestnuts
directions: Cook the chopped onions in the oil for 2 minutes.
Add the peas and water chestnuts.
Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Add the hot chicken stock, m.s.g. and dissolved cornstarch (mix cornstarch and water).
Add a little soy sauce if desired.
Stir and as soon as the sauce is transparent, serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: lazy u chocolate cake
directions: Mix 2 sticks margarine, 4 tablespoons cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to rapid boil.
Pour over flour mixture (2 cups sugar and plain flour) and stir well.
Don't use mixer.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 16 x 11-inch baking pan.
Cook at 375° about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinate meat for at least one hour.
The longer, the better. Grill.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey with instant beef bouillon and coarsely diced onions.
Add kidney beans, diced tomatoes and V-8 juice. Cook on medium heat in large skillet for 45 minutes.
Serving for 6.

title: versatile whole wheat bread
directions: With dough hook combine water, 7 cups of flour and yeast.
Add remaining ingredients and enough flour until dough cleans from side of bowl.
Knead 6 minutes (10 minutes by hand); form loaves and place in pans.
Let rise to near double.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
If mixed by hand, cover and let rise to double.
Punch down; let rest 15 minutes.
Second rising in bowl makes finer textured bread.
Form loaves and bake.
Use this versatile bread dough for many kinds of bread as follows:

title: chicken and rice gumbo(makes 10 servings)
directions: In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, heat chicken broth, chicken, corn, tomatoes, okra, rice and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except bacon, together until broccoli is totally coated with the mixture.
Sprinkle bacon on top; toss gently.

title: turkey tetrazzini(great for leftovers)
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter.
Add soup, stock and Worcestershire.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Slowly add cheese.
Add spaghetti to stock.
Mix; let stand 1 hour.
Add chicken and olives.
Pour into shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato rolls(from louise tuner)
directions: Stir
yeast
in
mixing bowl with warm water until dissolved. Stir
in sugar or Sweet 'N Low, salt, shortening, egg and potatoes.
Mix
flour
with
hands until dough is easy to handle. Knead
on
lightly	floured
board	until
smooth and elastic. Grease
dough
and	put
in
bowl
that
is slightly greased. Cover
with damp cloth and place in refrigerator for at
least
2 hours before baking or overnight.
About 2 hours before
baking, make out rolls on floured surface.	Let rise 1 1/2	to
hours. Cook
in
preheated 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes	or until brown.
Cover leftover dough with damp cloth and refrigerate. Makes about 1 dozen.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the chicken, in the crock. Stir well. Add the meat and stir well to coat. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 hours. Makes about 12 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute zucchini and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; set aside.
In same skillet, brown ground beef; drain fat. Stir flour, salt and pepper, then ketchup into meat.
Spoon meat over zucchini.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and top with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes until cheese is lightly brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Boil pineapple and Jell-O 5 minutes.
Let it cool.
Blend together cream cheese and apricot baby food.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients. Sprinkle chopped walnuts over the top, optional.

title: lemon sponge cake jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Chill until "livery." Whip until light and fluffy. Add lemon juice and sugar. Whip chilled milk. Fold in the jello mixture. Put 1/2 of the crushed wafers in bottom of cake pan; pat down. Add jello mixture and sprinkle the other 1/2 of wafers on top of jello mixture.

title: tex-mex skillet dinner
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta accents.
Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Sprinkle with cheese.
